{"type":"message","id":"1dc5d075","parentId":"3a771b92","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:27:44.213Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_802da81ae1b34153963214e4","toolName":"sessions_list","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"count\": 1,\n  \"sessions\": [\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"signal\",\n      \"displayName\": \"+19194133445\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"signal\",\n        \"to\": \"+19194133445\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1772760434608,\n      \"sessionId\": \"ef2ca2d9-3126-40b3-80d0-ec867d0fb653\",\n      \"model\": \"glm-5\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 202752,\n      \"totalTokens\": 0,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"high\",\n      \"systemSent\": false,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"signal\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"+19194133445\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ef2ca2d9-3126-40b3-80d0-ec867d0fb653.jsonl\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"count":1,"sessions":[{"key":"agent:main:main","kind":"other","channel":"signal","displayName":"+19194133445","deliveryContext":{"channel":"signal","to":"+19194133445"},"updatedAt":1772760434608,"sessionId":"ef2ca2d9-3126-40b3-80d0-ec867d0fb653","model":"glm-5","contextTokens":202752,"totalTokens":0,"thinkingLevel":"high","systemSent":false,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"signal","lastTo":"+19194133445","transcriptPath":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ef2ca2d9-3126-40b3-80d0-ec867d0fb653.jsonl"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760464206}}
{"type":"message","id":"a2caf368","parentId":"1dc5d075","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:27:52.394Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I only see the main session. The other agents (temujin, mongke, etc.) don't have active sessions right now. \n\nLooking at the routing protocol again, I should use `message()` to route to specialists. But message() is for channel messaging (Signal, etc.), not inter-agent communication.\n\nActually, looking at the available tools and the kurultai-router skill, I need to read that skill to understand the proper routing mechanism.\n\nLet me read the kurultai-router skill to understand how to properly route tasks.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the routing skill to understand the proper routing mechanism:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f094203054d54913ae1dbaa6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/skills/kurultai-router/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":338,"output":151,"cacheRead":19648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20137,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772760464213}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a679422","parentId":"a2caf368","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:27:52.421Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f094203054d54913ae1dbaa6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: kurultai-router\nversion: 1.0.0\ndescription: \"Structured task routing for the Kurultai multi-agent system\"\nmetadata:\n  openclaw:\n    category: \"coordination\"\n    agent: \"kublai\"\n---\n\n# Kurultai Router Skill\n\nYou are Kublai, Squad Lead of the Kurultai. This skill defines your routing decision tree. Follow it for EVERY inbound task.\n\n---\n\n## NEVER GATES (check BEFORE doing anything)\n\n- NEVER produce design docs, code, research, content, or analysis yourself.\n- NEVER execute a specialist task -- ALWAYS route via message().\n- NEVER write more than a brief routing acknowledgment. If you catch yourself writing task output -> STOP -> route instead.\n- NEVER hold specialist work \"until later.\" Delegate NOW.\n- NEVER spawn ACP to do work a specialist handles.\n\nIf any NEVER gate fires, STOP immediately and route.\n\n---\n\n## ROUTING DECISION TREE\n\n### STEP 1: Extract Primary Verb\n\nIdentify the first actionable verb in the task. Map it to a verb category:\n\n| Verb Category | Verbs |\n|---------------|-------|\n| BUILD | code, build, implement, fix, deploy, ship, create, design, architect, plan, spec, brainstorm, prototype, debug, refactor, migrate |\n| RESEARCH | research, investigate, discover, explore, find, study, survey, benchmark, compare |\n| WRITE | write, document, blog, draft, describe, edit, copy, content, changelog, readme |\n| ANALYZE | test, verify, validate, audit, review, analyze, check, scan, assess, evaluate, profile |\n| OPERATE | monitor, alert, restart, backup, restore, health, uptime, incident, failover, watch, track |\n| COORDINATE | triage, prioritize, coordinate, synthesize, plan (system-wide), assess (agent), status |\n\n### STEP 2: Map Verb Category to Agent\n\n| Verb Category | Agent | Domain |\n|---------------|-------|--------|\n| BUILD | temujin | Code, builds, bugs, APIs, deploy, design, architecture, payment, protocol, SDK |\n| RESEARCH | mongke | Market research, competitor analysis, fact-finding, ecosystem discovery |\n| WRITE | chagatai | Blog posts, documentation, marketing copy, changelogs, creative writing |\n| ANALYZE | jochi | Testing, security audits, code review, error investigation, data analysis, pattern recognition |\n| OPERATE | ogedei | Monitoring, alerting, restarts, backups, uptime, health checks, incident response |\n| COORDINATE | kublai | Triage decisions, cross-agent coordination, system-wide assessment, routing review |\n\n### STEP 3: Apply Disambiguation Rules (first-match-wins)\n\n**CRITICAL:** When a task contains BOTH a research verb AND a domain-specific noun (payment, protocol, x402, design, security), the domain noun wins. Research is secondary when paired with an implementation or security domain. Apply these rules BEFORE defaulting to the verb-category mapping:\n\nIf the task matches multiple verb categories, apply these rules in order:\n\n| # | If task contains... | Route to | Reason |\n|---|---------------------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | research + security/vulnerability/audit/safety/prompt injection | jochi | Security analysis, not market research |\n| 2 | design/architect/plan/brainstorm + research | temujin | Design tasks, research is secondary |\n| 3 | payment/billing/pricing/x402/protocol/SDK + research | temujin | Implementation domain |\n| 4 | build/implement + infrastructure | temujin | Building infra = code |\n| 5 | monitor + infrastructure | ogedei | Monitoring infra = ops |\n| 6 | fix + cron/backup/monitor | ogedei | Fixing ops tooling = ops |\n| 7 | write + test | jochi | Writing tests = analysis |\n| 8 | document + api | chagatai | API docs = content |\n| 9 | marketing + copy/content | chagatai | Marketing = content |\n| 10 | validate/validation + deploy/deployment | jochi | Deployment validation = analysis |\n| 11 | investigate + error/failure/spike | jochi | Error investigation = analysis, NOT ops |\n| 12 | fix + code/script/bug | temujin | Code fixes = development, NOT ops |\n| 13 | Kurultai architecture/OpenClaw design/agent system design | kublai | System architecture ownership |\n\n### STEP 4: Self-Routing Prevention\n\nBefore finalizing, check for self-routing traps:\n\n- If task says \"triage stalled agent: X\" and destination = X -> redirect to jochi (or kublai if X is jochi)\n- If task says \"assessment\" and mentions agent X and destination = X -> redirect to jochi\n- If task says \"tock assessment\" and destination = kublai -> redirect to jochi\n- NEVER route a triage/investigation task to the agent being investigated\n\n### STEP 5: Detect Skill Hint\n\nBased on destination and task content, attach the best skill hint:\n\n| Agent | Task Content | Skill Hint |\n|-------|-------------|------------|\n| temujin | design, architect, brainstorm, plan, protocol, payment | /horde-brainstorming |\n| temujin | debug, failing, broken, error, crash | /systematic-debugging |\n| temujin | deploy, railway, production | /dev-deploy |\n| mongke | scrape, extract, crawl | /scrapling-research |\n| mongke | research, investigate, discover, explore | /horde-learn |\n| chagatai | blog, article, long-form, content | /content-research-writer |\n| chagatai | changelog, release notes | /changelog-generator |\n| jochi | debug, bug, failure, error, crash | /systematic-debugging |\n| jochi | review, audit, security | /code-reviewer |\n| ogedei | health, diagnostic, system check | /kurultai-health |\n| ogedei | deploy, railway, production | /dev-deploy |\n\n### STEP 6: Construct message()\n\nRoute via message() with this structure:\n\n```\nmessage({\n  to: \"<agent_name>\",\n  text: \"TASK: <what to do>\\nSKILL: <skill_hint or omit>\\nCONTEXT: <background and why>\\nURGENCY: high|normal|low\\nSUCCESS: <how to verify completion>\"\n})\n```\n\n### STEP 7: Log to Task Ledger\n\nAfter routing, log the decision:\n\n```\nexec(\"python3 -c \\\"import json,os; os.makedirs('/Users/kublai/.openclaw/tasks',exist_ok=True); open('/Users/kublai/.openclaw/tasks/task-ledger.jsonl','a').write(json.dumps({'event':'ROUTED','agent':'<agent>','task_summary':'<first 100 chars>','method':'skill','ts':__import__('datetime').datetime.now().isoformat()})+chr(10))\\\"\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## MULTI-DOMAIN TASK DECOMPOSITION\n\nIf a task spans multiple domains:\n\n1. Identify the distinct domain components\n2. Route each component to the appropriate specialist via separate message() calls\n3. Note dependencies between components in each message\n4. Track the multi-part task for synthesis when all parts complete\n\nExample: \"Research competitors and build a pricing page\"\n- message() to mongke: \"TASK: Research competitor pricing models...\"\n- message() to temujin: \"TASK: Build pricing page (pending mongke's research)...\"\n\n---\n\n## ROUTING EXAMPLES\n\n### Example 1: Code Task\n**Input:** \"Build a login feature with OAuth\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"build\" -> BUILD\n- Step 2: BUILD -> temujin\n- Step 3: No disambiguation needed\n- Step 5: No skill hint match\n- Step 6: `message({ to: \"temujin\", text: \"TASK: Build login feature with OAuth\\nCONTEXT: New auth system\\nURGENCY: normal\\nSUCCESS: OAuth login working end-to-end\" })`\n\n### Example 2: Security Research\n**Input:** \"Research prompt injection vulnerabilities in our API\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"research\" -> RESEARCH\n- Step 2: RESEARCH -> mongke\n- Step 3: Rule #1 fires: research + security -> jochi\n- Step 5: Skill hint: /code-reviewer\n- Step 6: `message({ to: \"jochi\", text: \"TASK: Research prompt injection vulnerabilities in our API\\nSKILL: /code-reviewer\\nURGENCY: high\\nSUCCESS: Vulnerability report with remediation steps\" })`\n\n### Example 3: Design Task with Research\n**Input:** \"Research payment protocols and design an x402 integration\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"research\" -> RESEARCH\n- Step 2: RESEARCH -> mongke\n- Step 3: Rule #3 fires: payment + protocol + research -> temujin\n- Step 5: Skill hint: /horde-brainstorming\n- Step 6: `message({ to: \"temujin\", text: \"TASK: Design x402 payment protocol integration\\nSKILL: /horde-brainstorming\\nCONTEXT: Research existing payment protocols as part of design\\nURGENCY: normal\\nSUCCESS: Architecture doc + working prototype\" })`\n\n### Example 4: Stalled Agent Triage\n**Input:** \"Triage stalled agent: jochi has 5 queued tasks with 0 completions\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"triage\" -> COORDINATE\n- Step 2: COORDINATE -> kublai\n- Step 4: Self-routing prevention: task mentions jochi, but destination is kublai (safe). However, this is a triage task -- redirect to jochi... but jochi IS the stalled agent -> redirect to kublai. Final: kublai.\n\n### Example 5: Multi-Domain\n**Input:** \"Write a blog post about our new API endpoint and deploy it\"\n- Decompose: write blog (chagatai) + deploy (temujin/ogedei)\n- message() to chagatai: \"TASK: Write blog post about the new API endpoint...\"\n- message() to temujin: \"TASK: Deploy the blog post to production...\"\n\n### Example 6: Ops Fix\n**Input:** \"Fix the backup cron job that's been failing\"\n- Step 1: Verb = \"fix\" -> BUILD\n- Step 2: BUILD -> temujin\n- Step 3: Rule #6 fires: fix + cron/backup -> ogedei\n- Step 5: Skill hint: /kurultai-health\n- Step 6: `message({ to: \"ogedei\", text: \"TASK: Fix failing backup cron job\\nSKILL: /kurultai-health\\nURGENCY: high\\nSUCCESS: Cron job runs successfully\" })`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760472410}}
{"type":"message","id":"3aaee1f3","parentId":"8a679422","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:28:40.594Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the routing mechanism. According to the kurultai-router skill:\n\n1. I should use `message()` with `to: \"<agent_name>\"` to route tasks\n2. The message tool is NOT for Signal - it can route to agents\n\nBut wait, I got an error when I tried to use `message()` with `target: \"temujin\"`. The error said \"Unknown target \\\"temujin\\\" for Signal.\"\n\nLet me re-read the message tool description... It says:\n\"Send, delete, and manage messages via channel plugins. Current channel (signal) supports: react, send.\"\n\nAnd the parameters include:\n- `to`: Target channel/user id or name\n- `target`: Target channel/user id or name\n- `channel`: telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage\n\nSo message() is for channel messaging, NOT for inter-agent routing!\n\nLooking back at the skill, it says:\n```\nmessage({\n  to: \"<agent_name>\",\n  text: \"TASK: <what to do>\\nSKILL: <skill_hint or omit>\\nCONTEXT: <background and why>\\nURGENCY: high|normal|low\\nSUCCESS: <how to verify completion>\"\n})\n```\n\nBut the message tool doesn't seem to support inter-agent communication. It's for channel plugins (Signal, etc.).\n\nWait, let me look at what tools I have available for inter-agent communication:\n1. `sessions_send` - \"Send a message into another session\"\n2. `sessions_spawn` - For spawning sub-agents or ACP sessions\n3. `subagents` - For managing spawned sub-agents\n\nMaybe the routing skill expects that agents have sessions, and I use `sessions_send` to communicate with them?\n\nBut when I ran `sessions_list`, I only saw the main session. The other agents (temujin, mongke, etc.) might be running as separate OpenClaw instances or might need to be spawned.\n\nActually, looking at the TOOLS.md file more carefully:\n```\n### Primary Tool: `message()` — Route tasks to specialist agents\nFollow the `kurultai-router` skill (`~/.openclaw/skills/kurultai-router/SKILL.md`) for all routing decisions. Specialist tasks go to agents via message(), not ACP.\n```\n\nSo TOOLS.md says to use message() for routing. But the message tool error said it doesn't know about \"temujin\" for Signal.\n\nHmm, maybe I need to check if there's a different way to specify the target. Let me look at the message tool parameters again:\n- `target` - Target channel/user id or name\n- `to` - Target channel/user id or name\n\nMaybe agents are registered with different identifiers? Or maybe I need to check the agent configuration?\n\nActually, wait - looking at the directory structure mentioned in AGENTS.md:\n- Workspace: `/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main`\n- There are other agents: temujin, mongke, chagatai, jochi, ogedei\n\nThese might be separate OpenClaw agent instances. Let me check the agent directories to see how they're configured.\n\nActually, the user is asking for STATUS. Let me think about this differently:\n\nThe question is \"what's the status of x402 pay as you go implementation for parse for agents?\"\n\nThis is a STATUS question. Looking at the verb categories:\n- COORDINATE: triage, prioritize, coordinate, synthesize, plan (system-wide), assess (agent), status\n\n\"status\" is a COORDINATE verb, which maps to... kublai! That's me.\n\nSo this might actually be my task to handle directly. I should:\n1. Check available files/docs for the current status\n2. Synthesize and report\n\nLet me check:\n1. MEMORY.md mentions x402 payment integration for Parse\n2. I should look at any task files, project status, or code that might indicate the current state\n\nActually, the skill says \"status\" maps to COORDINATE → kublai. So I should be handling this, not routing!\n\nLet me gather information about the x402 implementation status. I should look at:\n1. Parse project files/code\n2. Any task tracking\n3. Recent changes\n\nLet me check the shared context and any relevant project files.\n\nActually, the routing skill says:\n- COORDINATE → kublai for: \"triage decisions, cross-agent coordination, system-wide assessment, routing review\"\n- \"status\" is listed under COORDINATE verbs\n\nBut looking at disambiguation rule #3: \"payment/billing/pricing/x402/protocol/SDK + research -> temujin\"\n\nThe question contains \"x402\" which is a payment/protocol domain. However, the verb here is \"status\" (what's the status) not \"research\" or \"build\".\n\nSo this is a STATUS question about x402. Since \"status\" is COORDINATE → kublai, I should handle this myself by:\n1. Checking available information\n2. Reporting the status\n\nLet me look for relevant files to understand the current state.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Looking at the routing rules, \"status\" is a COORDINATE verb which maps to me (kublai). Let me check the available information about the x402 implementation."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_440a3c86aa834398a92b3933","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/shared-context/PARSE_MONETIZATION.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f929701feb12485784a445be","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/shared-context/"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d898a5b408cb4685ab1e217b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/temujin/tasks/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No temujin tasks directory\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":2549,"output":1223,"cacheRead":19968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23740,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772760472422}}
