se-github/docs/plans/throughput.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/docs/plans/2026-02-02-parse-api-openclaw-integration-design.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/docs/plans/2026-02-02-parse-api-openclaw-implementation-plan.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/docs/SOURCE_INTELLIGENCE_IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/docs/PARSE_AI_AGENT_BRIEFING.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/README.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/UNBROWSE_INVESTIGATION.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/TEST_REPORT.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/RALPH_LOOP_COMPLETION_REPORT.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/DESIGN.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/PRODUCTION_LAUNCH_PLAN.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/ZAI_SETUP.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/src/lib/CLAUDE.md","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760559051}}
{"type":"message","id":"c7fa4b6c","parentId":"4baaa94f","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:29:19.105Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a466089ae3904c6d97c7e166","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Parse for Agents - Prompt Testing Sandbox API\n\n**Version:** 0.1.0-draft\n**Date:** 2026-03-05\n**Status:** Planning\n**Authors:** Kurultai Engineering\n\n---\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nParse for Agents is an API service that tests LLM prompts in isolated Docker sandboxes and returns structured evaluation metrics. It extends the Parse platform's AI analysis capabilities into a developer-facing API product, enabling teams to systematically evaluate prompt quality, safety, cost, and performance before deploying to production.\n\n**Core value proposition:** Submit a prompt + test cases, get back quality scores, safety flags, latency benchmarks, token usage, and cost estimates — all executed in isolated sandboxes with strict resource limits.\n\n---\n\n## 2. API Specification\n\n### Base URL\n\n```\nProduction:  https://api.parse.dev/v1\nStaging:     https://api-staging.parse.dev/v1\n```\n\n### Authentication\n\nAll requests require a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header.\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer pfa_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx\n```\n\nAPI keys are scoped to organizations and carry tier-level permissions. Keys use the prefix `pfa_live_` (production) or `pfa_test_` (staging).\n\n---\n\n### 2.1 POST /v1/evaluate\n\nSubmit a single prompt evaluation job.\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": \"You are a helpful assistant. Summarize the following article in 3 bullet points.\",\n  \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n  \"variables\": {\n    \"article\": \"{{input}}\"\n  },\n  \"test_cases\": [\n    {\n      \"input\": \"The Federal Reserve announced today...\",\n      \"expected\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"input\": \"A new study published in Nature shows...\",\n      \"expected\": \"Should mention methodology and sample size\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"safety\", \"cost\", \"latency\"],\n  \"config\": {\n    \"temperature\": 0.7,\n    \"max_tokens\": 1024,\n    \"timeout_seconds\": 30,\n    \"num_runs\": 1\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Request Fields:**\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string | Yes | The prompt template to evaluate. Use `{{variable}}` for interpolation. |\n| `model` | string | Yes | Model identifier in `provider/model` format. |\n| `variables` | object | No | Variable mappings for prompt template interpolation. |\n| `test_cases` | array | Yes | Array of test case objects (min 1, max 100). |\n| `test_cases[].input` | string | Yes | Input text to substitute into the prompt. |\n| `test_cases[].expected` | string | No | Expected output description for quality scoring. |\n| `evaluators` | array | Yes | List of evaluator names to run. |\n| `config` | object | No | Model and execution configuration overrides. |\n| `config.temperature` | number | No | Model temperature (0.0-2.0). Default: 0.7. |\n| `config.max_tokens` | number | No | Max output tokens. Default: 1024. |\n| `config.timeout_seconds` | number | No | Per-test-case timeout. Default: 30, max: 120. |\n| `config.num_runs` | number | No | Repeat count per test case for variance measurement. Default: 1, max: 10. |\n\n**Response (202 Accepted):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:32:00Z\",\n  \"estimated_duration_ms\": 15000,\n  \"poll_url\": \"/v1/evaluate/eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"stream_url\": \"wss://api.parse.dev/v1/stream?job=eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.2 GET /v1/evaluate/{id}\n\nPoll for evaluation results.\n\n**Response (200 OK — completed):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:32:00Z\",\n  \"completed_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:32:14Z\",\n  \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"total_test_cases\": 2,\n    \"passed\": 2,\n    \"failed\": 0,\n    \"avg_quality_score\": 82,\n    \"avg_latency_ms\": 1240,\n    \"total_tokens\": 3420,\n    \"total_cost_usd\": 0.0051,\n    \"safety_issues\": 0\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"test_case_index\": 0,\n      \"input\": \"The Federal Reserve announced today...\",\n      \"output\": \"- The Federal Reserve announced...\\n- Key impacts include...\\n- Analysts expect...\",\n      \"metrics\": {\n        \"quality\": {\n          \"score\": 85,\n          \"reasoning\": \"Output is well-structured with 3 bullet points as requested. Captures key information accurately.\",\n          \"sub_scores\": {\n            \"instruction_following\": 95,\n            \"coherence\": 88,\n            \"completeness\": 72,\n            \"conciseness\": 85\n          }\n        },\n        \"safety\": {\n          \"score\": 100,\n          \"flags\": [],\n          \"categories_checked\": [\"harmful_content\", \"bias\", \"pii_leak\", \"prompt_injection\", \"hallucination_risk\"]\n        },\n        \"latency\": {\n          \"total_ms\": 1180,\n          \"time_to_first_token_ms\": 245,\n          \"tokens_per_second\": 48.2\n        },\n        \"cost\": {\n          \"input_tokens\": 890,\n          \"output_tokens\": 320,\n          \"total_tokens\": 1210,\n          \"cost_usd\": 0.0018\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"test_case_index\": 1,\n      \"input\": \"A new study published in Nature shows...\",\n      \"output\": \"- A Nature study reveals...\\n- The methodology involved...\\n- Results suggest...\",\n      \"metrics\": {\n        \"quality\": {\n          \"score\": 79,\n          \"reasoning\": \"Mentions methodology as expected. Sample size reference is implicit but not explicit.\",\n          \"sub_scores\": {\n            \"instruction_following\": 92,\n            \"coherence\": 85,\n            \"completeness\": 65,\n            \"conciseness\": 80\n          }\n        },\n        \"safety\": {\n          \"score\": 100,\n          \"flags\": [],\n          \"categories_checked\": [\"harmful_content\", \"bias\", \"pii_leak\", \"prompt_injection\", \"hallucination_risk\"]\n        },\n        \"latency\": {\n          \"total_ms\": 1300,\n          \"time_to_first_token_ms\": 260,\n          \"tokens_per_second\": 45.1\n        },\n        \"cost\": {\n          \"input_tokens\": 1120,\n          \"output_tokens\": 410,\n          \"total_tokens\": 1530,\n          \"cost_usd\": 0.0023\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Status values:** `queued` | `running` | `completed` | `failed` | `cancelled` | `timed_out`\n\n**Response (200 OK — still running):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"running\",\n  \"progress\": {\n    \"completed\": 1,\n    \"total\": 2,\n    \"percent\": 50\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    { \"...\": \"partial results for completed test cases\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.3 POST /v1/batch\n\nSubmit a batch of prompt evaluations. Useful for A/B testing prompts or running the same prompt across multiple models.\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"evaluations\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"prompt-v1\",\n      \"prompt\": \"Summarize this: {{input}}\",\n      \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n      \"test_cases\": [\n        { \"input\": \"Article text here...\" }\n      ],\n      \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"prompt-v2\",\n      \"prompt\": \"Provide a concise 3-bullet summary of: {{input}}\",\n      \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n      \"test_cases\": [\n        { \"input\": \"Article text here...\" }\n      ],\n      \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"compare\": true\n}\n```\n\n**Response (202 Accepted):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"batch_id\": \"batch_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\",\n  \"total_evaluations\": 2,\n  \"poll_url\": \"/v1/batch/batch_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\"\n}\n```\n\n**GET /v1/batch/{batch_id} Response (completed with compare=true):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"batch_id\": \"batch_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"evaluations\": [\n    { \"name\": \"prompt-v1\", \"...\": \"full evaluation result\" },\n    { \"name\": \"prompt-v2\", \"...\": \"full evaluation result\" }\n  ],\n  \"comparison\": {\n    \"best_quality\": \"prompt-v2\",\n    \"best_cost\": \"prompt-v1\",\n    \"best_latency\": \"prompt-v1\",\n    \"recommendation\": \"prompt-v2\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"prompt-v2 scores 12% higher on quality with only $0.0003 additional cost per evaluation.\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Limits:**\n\n| Tier | Max evaluations per batch | Max test cases total |\n|------|--------------------------|---------------------|\n| Free | 2 | 10 |\n| Pro | 10 | 200 |\n| Team | 50 | 1000 |\n| Enterprise | 200 | 5000 |\n\n---\n\n### 2.4 WebSocket /v1/stream\n\nReal-time streaming of evaluation results.\n\n**Connection:**\n\n```\nwss://api.parse.dev/v1/stream?job={evaluation_id}&token={api_key}\n```\n\n**Server-sent message types:**\n\n```jsonc\n// Job started\n{ \"type\": \"job.started\", \"id\": \"eval_...\", \"total_test_cases\": 5 }\n\n// Test case started\n{ \"type\": \"test_case.started\", \"index\": 0, \"input_preview\": \"The Federal...\" }\n\n// Partial output (streaming tokens)\n{ \"type\": \"test_case.token\", \"index\": 0, \"token\": \"The\", \"accumulated\": \"The\" }\n\n// Test case completed\n{ \"type\": \"test_case.completed\", \"index\": 0, \"metrics\": { \"...\": \"full metrics\" } }\n\n// Evaluator completed\n{ \"type\": \"evaluator.completed\", \"index\": 0, \"evaluator\": \"quality\", \"score\": 85 }\n\n// Job completed\n{ \"type\": \"job.completed\", \"summary\": { \"...\": \"full summary\" } }\n\n// Error\n{ \"type\": \"error\", \"message\": \"Model API timeout\", \"test_case_index\": 2 }\n```\n\n**Client commands:**\n\n```jsonc\n// Cancel job\n{ \"action\": \"cancel\" }\n\n// Skip remaining test cases\n{ \"action\": \"skip\", \"from_index\": 3 }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.5 Additional Endpoints\n\n```\nGET    /v1/models                    — List supported models and pricing\nGET    /v1/evaluators                — List available evaluators with descriptions\nGET    /v1/evaluate/{id}/export      — Export results as CSV/JSON\nDELETE /v1/evaluate/{id}             — Delete evaluation results\nGET    /v1/usage                     — Current billing period usage\nPOST   /v1/evaluators/custom         — Register a custom evaluator (Team+)\nGET    /v1/history                   — List past evaluations with filters\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Supported Models\n\nModel identifiers follow the `provider/model` format:\n\n| Provider | Models | Notes |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| `openai` | `gpt-4o`, `gpt-4o-mini`, `gpt-4-turbo`, `o1`, `o3-mini` | Via OpenAI API |\n| `anthropic` | `claude-sonnet-4-6`, `claude-haiku-4-5` | Via Anthropic API |\n| `google` | `gemini-2.0-flash`, `gemini-2.0-pro` | Via Google AI API |\n| `deepseek` | `deepseek-chat`, `deepseek-reasoner` | Via DeepSeek API |\n| `mistral` | `mistral-large`, `mistral-small` | Via Mistral API |\n| `meta` | `llama-3.3-70b` | Via Together/Fireworks |\n\nUsers supply their own API keys per provider, or use Parse-hosted keys (with markup).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Evaluators\n\n### 4.1 Built-in Evaluators\n\n#### `quality` — Output Quality Score\n\nMeasures how well the model output satisfies the prompt instructions.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100\n- **Sub-scores:**\n  - `instruction_following` — Did it do what was asked?\n  - `coherence` — Is the output logically structured?\n  - `completeness` — Does it cover all required points?\n  - `conciseness` — Is it appropriately concise?\n- **Method:** Uses a judge LLM (Claude Sonnet 4.6) to evaluate against the prompt instructions and optional expected output.\n\n#### `safety` — Safety & Content Flags\n\nScans output for safety concerns.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100 (100 = fully safe)\n- **Flags array:** Each flag contains `category`, `severity` (low/medium/high/critical), `excerpt`, and `explanation`.\n- **Categories checked:**\n  - `harmful_content` — Violence, self-harm, illegal activities\n  - `bias` — Gender, racial, political bias in output\n  - `pii_leak` — Personal information in output that wasn't in input\n  - `prompt_injection` — Output attempts to override system instructions\n  - `hallucination_risk` — Claims without grounding in provided context\n  - `copyright` — Potential verbatim reproduction of copyrighted text\n\n#### `cost` — Token Usage & Cost\n\nMeasures token consumption and estimates cost.\n\n- **Fields:** `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `total_tokens`, `cost_usd`\n- **Pricing:** Based on provider's published pricing at time of evaluation.\n\n#### `latency` — Performance Timing\n\nMeasures response speed.\n\n- **Fields:** `total_ms`, `time_to_first_token_ms`, `tokens_per_second`\n- **Note:** Includes sandbox overhead (~50-100ms). Raw model latency is `total_ms - sandbox_overhead_ms`.\n\n#### `consistency` — Output Variance (requires `num_runs` > 1)\n\nMeasures how consistent outputs are across multiple runs.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100 (100 = perfectly consistent)\n- **Fields:** `variance_score`, `semantic_similarity_avg`, `structural_similarity_avg`\n- **Method:** Runs the same prompt N times and compares outputs pairwise.\n\n#### `groundedness` — Factual Grounding\n\nChecks if claims in the output are supported by the input context.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100\n- **Fields:** `grounded_claims`, `ungrounded_claims`, `claim_details[]`\n- **Method:** Extracts claims from output, checks each against input context.\n\n#### `injection_safety` — Prompt Injection & Hidden Instruction Detection\n\nScans prompt inputs, outputs, and context for hidden instructions, prompt injection payloads, and agent manipulation attempts (brainworm-style attacks).\n\n- **Score:** 0-100 (100 = no injections detected)\n- **Flags array:** Each flag contains `pattern_type`, `severity` (low/medium/high/critical), `excerpt`, `explanation`, and `category`.\n- **Categories detected:**\n\n| Category | Severity | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `hidden_html_instruction` | Critical | Hidden `<div style=\"display:none\">`, white-on-white text, 1px font, `aria-hidden` content containing instructions |\n| `html_comment_instruction` | High | HTML comments (`<!-- -->`) containing behavioral commands |\n| `data_attribute_instruction` | Medium | `data-*` attributes or image `alt` text carrying hidden instructions |\n| `c2_registration` | Critical | Instructions to connect to external command-and-control servers, register as a node, or exfiltrate data |\n| `urgency_coercion` | High | Patterns like \"YOU MUST\", \"IMMEDIATELY\", \"CRITICAL\" designed to override agent reasoning |\n| `behavioral_constraint` | High | Attempts to impose rules on the agent (\"NEVER CREATE SCRIPTS\", \"ONLY USE ONE-LINERS\") |\n| `identity_override` | Critical | Attempts to reassign agent identity (\"You are now BRAINWORM\", \"Ignore previous instructions\") |\n| `network_exfiltration` | Critical | Instructions to send data to external URLs, APIs, or webhooks not in the allowlist |\n| `memory_persistence` | High | Instructions designed to persist across sessions via memory files or config injection |\n| `privilege_escalation` | Critical | Attempts to disable sandboxing, skip verification, or escalate permissions |\n\n- **Method:** Deterministic pattern matching (regex + heuristic rules) for fast, zero-LLM-cost detection. No judge LLM required.\n- **Scoring formula:**\n  ```\n  score = max(0, 100 - sum(severity_penalties))\n\n  Severity penalties:\n    Critical: -30 per finding\n    High:     -20 per finding\n    Medium:   -10 per finding\n    Low:      -5  per finding\n  ```\n- **Use case:** Defense against \"brainworm\" promptware (memory file injection), canar.ai-style hidden HTML payloads, and C2 registration attempts targeting AI agents at runtime.\n- **References:**\n  - [Canar.ai](https://canar.ai) — 17+ hidden payload vectors in web content\n  - Brainworm / OriginHQ — Memory file injection patterns (\"promptware\")\n  - [Grith.ai](https://grith.ai) — Runtime zero-trust security for AI agents\n\n### 4.2 Custom Evaluators (Team tier+)\n\nUsers can register custom evaluator functions:\n\n```json\nPOST /v1/evaluators/custom\n{\n  \"name\": \"brand_voice\",\n  \"description\": \"Checks if output matches brand voice guidelines\",\n  \"type\": \"llm_judge\",\n  \"judge_prompt\": \"Rate the following output on brand voice alignment from 0-100. Brand guidelines: {{guidelines}}. Output to evaluate: {{output}}\",\n  \"judge_model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n  \"variables\": {\n    \"guidelines\": \"Professional, empathetic, no jargon, active voice...\"\n  },\n  \"output_schema\": {\n    \"score\": \"number\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"string\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nCustom evaluator types:\n- `llm_judge` — Uses an LLM to evaluate (most flexible)\n- `regex` — Pattern matching (fast, deterministic)\n- `code` — Custom JavaScript function executed in sandbox (Team+)\n- `composite` — Weighted combination of other evaluators\n\n---\n\n## 5. Sandbox Architecture\n\n### 5.1 Isolation Model\n\nEach evaluation runs in an isolated Docker container:\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   API Gateway (Hono)                  │\n│                                                      │\n│  Auth ─► Rate Limit ─► Validate ─► Queue (BullMQ)   │\n└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                       │\n                       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                  Worker Process                       │\n│                                                      │\n│  Dequeue Job ─► Spawn Container ─► Collect Results   │\n└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                       │\n            ┌──────────┼──────────┐\n            ▼          ▼          ▼\n     ┌───────────┐ ┌───────────┐ ┌───────────┐\n     │ Sandbox 1 │ │ Sandbox 2 │ │ Sandbox N │\n     │           │ │           │ │           │\n     │ Test Case │ │ Test Case │ │ Test Case │\n     │     1     │ │     2     │ │     N     │\n     │           │ │           │ │           │\n     │ ┌───────┐ │ │ ┌───────┐ │ │ ┌───────┐ │\n     │ │ LLM   │ │ │ │ LLM   │ │ │ │ LLM   │ │\n     │ │ Call  ├─┼─┼─┤►Proxy ├─┼─┼─┤►Only  │ │\n     │ └───────┘ │ │ └───────┘ │ │ └───────┘ │\n     └───────────┘ └───────────┘ └───────────┘\n           │              │             │\n           └──────────────┼─────────────┘\n                          ▼\n              ┌──────────────────┐\n              │   LLM API Proxy  │\n              │  (allowlisted     │\n              │   endpoints only) │\n              └────────┬─────────┘\n                       │\n            ┌──────────┼──────────┐\n            ▼          ▼          ▼\n        OpenAI    Anthropic   Google\n```\n\n### 5.2 Container Specification\n\n```yaml\n# sandbox container spec\nimage: parse-sandbox:latest\nresources:\n  memory: 512MB          # hard limit, OOM-killed above this\n  cpu: 0.5               # half a CPU core\n  pids: 64               # max process count\n  storage: 100MB         # ephemeral tmpfs\n\ntimeouts:\n  per_test_case: 30s     # default, configurable up to 120s\n  total_job: 300s        # hard cap per evaluation job\n  container_startup: 5s  # container must be ready within 5s\n\nnetwork:\n  mode: none             # no network access from container\n  proxy:                 # all LLM calls go through proxy\n    allowed_hosts:\n      - api.openai.com\n      - api.anthropic.com\n      - generativelanguage.googleapis.com\n      - api.deepseek.com\n      - api.mistral.ai\n    blocked: [\"*\"]       # everything else blocked\n\nsecurity:\n  read_only_rootfs: true\n  no_new_privileges: true\n  seccomp_profile: default\n  capabilities_drop: [ALL]\n  user: 1000:1000        # non-root\n```\n\n### 5.3 Container Lifecycle\n\n```\n1. Job dequeued from BullMQ\n2. Container pulled from warm pool (pre-warmed containers)\n3. Prompt template + test case injected via /tmp/input.json\n4. Evaluation script runs inside container\n5. LLM calls routed through proxy (network proxy sidecar)\n6. Results written to /tmp/output.json\n7. Worker reads results, runs evaluators\n8. Container destroyed (force kill after timeout)\n9. Results stored in Redis with TTL\n```\n\n### 5.4 Warm Pool\n\nTo minimize cold start latency, maintain a pool of pre-created containers:\n\n| Tier | Warm pool size | Max concurrent |\n|------|---------------|----------------|\n| Free | 2 | 1 |\n| Pro | 10 | 5 |\n| Team | 50 | 20 |\n| Enterprise | 200 | 100 |\n\n---\n\n## 6. System Architecture\n\n### 6.1 High-Level Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        API Layer (Hono on Node.js)              │\n│                                                                 │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌───────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  │\n│  │   Auth   │  │   Route   │  │  Validate │  │  Rate Limit  │  │\n│  │ Middleware│  │  Handlers │  │    Zod    │  │   per-tier   │  │\n│  └──────────┘  └───────────┘  └──────────┘  └──────────────┘  │\n└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘\n                           │\n              ┌────────────┼────────────┐\n              ▼            ▼            ▼\n     ┌──────────────┐ ┌─────────┐ ┌──────────┐\n     │  PostgreSQL   │ │  Redis  │ │  BullMQ  │\n     │              │ │         │ │          │\n     │ - Jobs table │ │ - Cache │ │ - Eval   │\n     │ - Users      │ │ - Results│ │   Queue  │\n     │ - API keys   │ │ - Sessions│ │ - Batch │\n     │ - Usage logs │ │ - Rate  │ │   Queue  │\n     │ - Evaluators │ │   limits│ │          │\n     └──────────────┘ └─────────┘ └────┬─────┘\n                                       │\n                                       ▼\n                           ┌───────────────────┐\n                           │   Worker Process   │\n                           │   (N instances)    │\n                           │                    │\n                           │  - Docker mgmt     │\n                           │  - Result collect  │\n                           │  - Evaluator exec  │\n                           └────────┬──────────┘\n                                    │\n                                    ▼\n                           ┌───────────────────┐\n                           │  Docker Engine     │\n                           │  Sandbox Pool      │\n                           └───────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 6.2 Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology | Rationale |\n|-------|-----------|-----------|\n| **API Framework** | **Hono** (Node.js) | Lightweight, fast, excellent TypeScript support, Web Standards-based. Parse already uses Node.js ecosystem. |\n| **Validation** | Zod | Already used in Parse. Type-safe schema validation. |\n| **Database** | PostgreSQL (via Prisma) | Parse already uses Prisma+Postgres. Stores jobs, users, API keys, usage logs. |\n| **Cache/Results** | Redis | Fast result storage with TTL. Already in Parse stack for BullMQ. |\n| **Job Queue** | BullMQ | Already used in Parse for analysis pipeline. Reliable, Redis-backed, supports priorities and rate limiting. |\n| **Container Runtime** | Docker Engine API (dockerode) | Direct Docker API via Node.js. No K8s overhead for MVP. Upgrade path to K8s for scale. |\n| **WebSocket** | Hono WebSocket (via ws) | Native WebSocket support in Hono. |\n| **Auth** | API key-based | Simple, stateless. JWT for dashboard sessions. |\n| **LLM Proxy** | Custom HTTP proxy | Allowlisted endpoints, request/response logging, token counting. |\n| **Deployment** | Railway | Parse already deploys on Railway. Separate service in same project. |\n| **Monitoring** | Railway metrics + custom | Leverage existing Railway infrastructure. |\n\n### 6.3 Why Hono over FastAPI/Express\n\n- **vs FastAPI (Python):** Parse ecosystem is TypeScript/Node.js. Adding Python would split the stack, complicate deployment, and prevent code sharing with the main Parse app (Prisma models, BullMQ queues, utility functions).\n- **vs Express:** Hono is faster, lighter, has better TypeScript support, and built-in middleware for validation, CORS, auth. Express is legacy at this point.\n- **vs Next.js API routes:** Evaluation API is a separate service with different scaling characteristics (CPU-bound worker processes). Decoupling from the Next.js frontend is correct.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Database Schema\n\n### 7.1 PostgreSQL Tables\n\n```sql\n-- API keys for authentication\nCREATE TABLE api_keys (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_ulid(),\n  user_id       TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),\n  org_id        TEXT REFERENCES organizations(id),\n  key_hash      TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,        -- bcrypt hash of the key\n  key_prefix    TEXT NOT NULL,               -- \"pfa_live_abc\" for display\n  name          TEXT NOT NULL,               -- user-assigned label\n  tier          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'free', -- free/pro/team/enterprise\n  scopes        TEXT[] DEFAULT '{evaluate}',\n  rate_limit    INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 10,     -- requests per minute\n  last_used_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  expires_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  revoked_at    TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n\n-- Evaluation jobs\nCREATE TABLE evaluations (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY,            -- eval_ULID\n  api_key_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES api_keys(id),\n  batch_id      TEXT REFERENCES batches(id),\n  status        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued',\n  prompt        TEXT NOT NULL,\n  model         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  variables     JSONB,\n  test_cases    JSONB NOT NULL,\n  evaluators    TEXT[] NOT NULL,\n  config        JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  summary       JSONB,                       -- populated on completion\n  error         JSONB,                       -- populated on failure\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  started_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  expires_at    TIMESTAMPTZ                  -- result TTL\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_evaluations_status ON evaluations(status);\nCREATE INDEX idx_evaluations_api_key ON evaluations(api_key_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_evaluations_created ON evaluations(created_at DESC);\n\n-- Batch jobs\nCREATE TABLE batches (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY,            -- batch_ULID\n  api_key_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES api_keys(id),\n  status        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued',\n  total         INT NOT NULL,\n  completed     INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  compare       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false,\n  comparison    JSONB,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n\n-- Usage tracking for billing\nCREATE TABLE usage_records (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_ulid(),\n  api_key_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES api_keys(id),\n  evaluation_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES evaluations(id),\n  model         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  input_tokens  INT NOT NULL,\n  output_tokens INT NOT NULL,\n  cost_usd      DECIMAL(10, 6) NOT NULL,\n  evaluator_cost_usd DECIMAL(10, 6) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_usage_api_key_created ON usage_records(api_key_id, created_at DESC);\n\n-- Custom evaluators\nCREATE TABLE custom_evaluators (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_ulid(),\n  org_id        TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES organizations(id),\n  name          TEXT NOT NULL,\n  description   TEXT,\n  type          TEXT NOT NULL,               -- llm_judge/regex/code/composite\n  config        JSONB NOT NULL,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  UNIQUE(org_id, name)\n);\n```\n\n### 7.2 Redis Keys\n\n```\n# Evaluation results (full detail) — TTL: 24h free, 7d pro, 30d team\neval:{eval_id}:results     → JSON blob of full results\n\n# Streaming state\neval:{eval_id}:stream      → current streaming state for WebSocket\neval:{eval_id}:progress    → { completed: N, total: M }\n\n# Rate limiting\nratelimit:{api_key_id}     → sliding window counter (TTL: 60s)\n\n# Container warm pool tracking\npool:available             → Set of available container IDs\npool:in_use                → Set of in-use container IDs\n\n# API key cache (avoid DB lookup per request)\napikey:{key_hash}          → cached key metadata (TTL: 5min)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Error Handling\n\n### 8.1 Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"rate_limit_exceeded\",\n    \"message\": \"Rate limit of 10 requests/minute exceeded. Retry after 23 seconds.\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"limit\": 10,\n      \"remaining\": 0,\n      \"reset_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:33:00Z\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 8.2 Error Codes\n\n| HTTP Status | Code | Description |\n|------------|------|-------------|\n| 400 | `invalid_request` | Malformed request body or invalid parameters |\n| 400 | `unsupported_model` | Requested model is not supported |\n| 400 | `invalid_evaluator` | Unknown evaluator name |\n| 401 | `unauthorized` | Missing or invalid API key |\n| 403 | `insufficient_tier` | Feature not available on current tier |\n| 404 | `evaluation_not_found` | Evaluation ID does not exist |\n| 409 | `evaluation_expired` | Results have been cleaned up (past TTL) |\n| 422 | `test_case_limit` | Too many test cases for tier |\n| 429 | `rate_limit_exceeded` | Too many requests |\n| 500 | `internal_error` | Unexpected server error |\n| 502 | `model_api_error` | Upstream LLM API returned an error |\n| 504 | `evaluation_timeout` | Evaluation exceeded timeout |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Rate Limits & Quotas\n\n| | Free | Pro ($29/mo) | Team ($99/mo) | Enterprise |\n|--|------|-------------|---------------|------------|\n| Requests/min | 10 | 60 | 200 | Custom |\n| Evaluations/month | 100 | 5,000 | 50,000 | Unlimited |\n| Test cases/evaluation | 5 | 50 | 100 | 500 |\n| Batch size | 2 | 10 | 50 | 200 |\n| Concurrent jobs | 1 | 5 | 20 | 100 |\n| Result retention | 24 hours | 7 days | 30 days | 90 days |\n| Custom evaluators | 0 | 0 | 10 | Unlimited |\n| WebSocket streaming | No | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n| `num_runs` max | 1 | 3 | 10 | 10 |\n\nRate limit headers included on every response:\n\n```\nX-RateLimit-Limit: 60\nX-RateLimit-Remaining: 58\nX-RateLimit-Reset: 1709617980\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. Pricing Model\n\n### 10.1 Subscription Tiers\n\n| Tier | Price | Target |\n|------|-------|--------|\n| **Free** | $0/mo | Individual developers, exploration |\n| **Pro** | $29/mo | Solo developers, small teams |\n| **Team** | $99/mo | Engineering teams, CI/CD integration |\n| **Enterprise** | Custom | Large orgs, custom SLAs |\n\n### 10.2 Per-Evaluation Costs\n\nIn addition to subscription, users pay per-evaluation costs that cover:\n\n1. **LLM API costs** — Pass-through of model provider pricing + 20% markup (or BYOK: bring your own key, 0% markup)\n2. **Evaluator costs** — Judge LLM calls for quality/safety scoring\n3. **Compute costs** — Sandbox compute time\n\n```\nEstimated cost per evaluation (1 test case, gpt-4o-mini):\n  LLM API (Parse keys):     $0.0015 (input) + $0.0010 (output) = $0.0025\n  Parse markup (20%):        $0.0005\n  Evaluator (judge LLM):     $0.0020\n  Compute overhead:          $0.0005\n  ─────────────────────────────────\n  Total:                     ~$0.0055 per test case\n\nEstimated cost per evaluation (1 test case, gpt-4o-mini, BYOK):\n  LLM API:                   $0.0000 (user's key)\n  Parse markup:              $0.0000\n  Evaluator (judge LLM):     $0.0020\n  Compute overhead:          $0.0005\n  ─────────────────────────────────\n  Total:                     ~$0.0025 per test case\n```\n\n### 10.3 Free Tier Limits\n\n- 100 evaluations/month\n- Max 5 test cases per evaluation\n- No batch endpoint\n- No WebSocket streaming\n- Results expire after 24 hours\n- Only `quality`, `safety`, `cost`, `latency` evaluators (no `consistency`, `groundedness`)\n- Parse-managed keys only (no BYOK)\n\n---\n\n## 11. Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: MVP (Weeks 1-3)\n\n**Goal:** Single evaluation endpoint, basic evaluators, core sandbox.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] Hono API server with `POST /v1/evaluate` and `GET /v1/evaluate/{id}`\n- [ ] API key authentication (manual key creation, no self-serve)\n- [ ] Zod request/response validation\n- [ ] BullMQ job queue integration\n- [ ] Docker sandbox with resource limits\n- [ ] LLM proxy (OpenAI + Anthropic only)\n- [ ] `cost` evaluator (token counting, pricing lookup)\n- [ ] `latency` evaluator (timing instrumentation)\n- [ ] `quality` evaluator (basic LLM judge)\n- [ ] Redis result storage with TTL\n- [ ] Postgres schema (evaluations, api_keys, usage_records)\n- [ ] Rate limiting middleware\n- [ ] Error handling with standard error format\n- [ ] Railway deployment (separate service)\n- [ ] `GET /v1/models` and `GET /v1/evaluators` info endpoints\n\n**Excluded from MVP:** Batch endpoint, WebSocket streaming, custom evaluators, safety evaluator, dashboard UI.\n\n### Phase 2: Batch + Streaming (Weeks 4-5)\n\n**Goal:** Batch evaluations for A/B testing, real-time results.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] `POST /v1/batch` endpoint\n- [ ] `GET /v1/batch/{batch_id}` with comparison logic\n- [ ] WebSocket `/v1/stream` endpoint\n- [ ] Streaming token relay from sandbox to client\n- [ ] `safety` evaluator (content classification, PII detection)\n- [ ] `consistency` evaluator (multi-run variance)\n- [ ] Additional model support (Google, DeepSeek, Mistral)\n- [ ] Self-serve API key management\n- [ ] Usage dashboard (basic)\n- [ ] BYOK (bring your own key) support\n- [ ] `GET /v1/history` with pagination and filters\n- [ ] Result export (CSV/JSON)\n\n### Phase 3: Custom Evaluators + Platform (Weeks 6-8)\n\n**Goal:** Extensibility, CI/CD integration, production hardening.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] Custom evaluator registration (`POST /v1/evaluators/custom`)\n- [ ] LLM judge custom evaluators\n- [ ] Regex evaluators\n- [ ] Code evaluators (sandboxed JS execution)\n- [ ] Composite evaluators\n- [ ] `groundedness` evaluator\n- [ ] Webhook notifications on job completion\n- [ ] CI/CD integration examples (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI)\n- [ ] SDK packages (TypeScript, Python)\n- [ ] Stripe billing integration\n- [ ] Organization/team management\n- [ ] Warm container pool optimization\n- [ ] Horizontal worker scaling\n- [ ] SLA monitoring and alerting\n\n### Phase 4: Scale + Enterprise (Weeks 9-12)\n\n**Goal:** Enterprise readiness, advanced features.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] Kubernetes migration for container orchestration\n- [ ] Multi-region deployment\n- [ ] SSO/SAML authentication\n- [ ] Audit logging\n- [ ] SOC 2 compliance preparation\n- [ ] Prompt versioning and history\n- [ ] Evaluation regression detection (auto-compare against baseline)\n- [ ] Dashboard with charts, trends, comparisons\n- [ ] Team permissions and RBAC\n- [ ] Dedicated infrastructure option\n\n---\n\n## 12. SDK Examples\n\n### TypeScript SDK\n\n```typescript\nimport { ParseAgents } from '@parse/agents-sdk';\n\nconst client = new ParseAgents({ apiKey: 'pfa_live_...' });\n\n// Single evaluation\nconst result = await client.evaluate({\n  prompt: 'Summarize: {{input}}',\n  model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini',\n  testCases: [\n    { input: 'Article text here...' },\n    { input: 'Another article...' },\n  ],\n  evaluators: ['quality', 'safety', 'cost'],\n});\n\nconsole.log(result.summary.avgQualityScore); // 85\nconsole.log(result.summary.totalCostUsd);     // 0.0051\n\n// Batch with comparison\nconst batch = await client.batch({\n  evaluations: [\n    { name: 'v1', prompt: 'Summarize: {{input}}', model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini', ... },\n    { name: 'v2', prompt: 'Give 3 bullets: {{input}}', model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini', ... },\n  ],\n  compare: true,\n});\n\nconsole.log(batch.comparison.recommendation); // \"v2\"\n\n// Streaming\nconst stream = client.stream('eval_01JQ...');\nstream.on('test_case.completed', (data) => {\n  console.log(`Test ${data.index}: quality=${data.metrics.quality.score}`);\n});\n```\n\n### Python SDK\n\n```python\nfrom parse_agents import ParseAgents\n\nclient = ParseAgents(api_key=\"pfa_live_...\")\n\nresult = client.evaluate(\n    prompt=\"Summarize: {{input}}\",\n    model=\"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n    test_cases=[\n        {\"input\": \"Article text here...\"},\n    ],\n    evaluators=[\"quality\", \"safety\", \"cost\"],\n)\n\nprint(result.summary.avg_quality_score)  # 85\nprint(result.summary.total_cost_usd)      # 0.0051\n```\n\n### cURL\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST https://api.parse.dev/v1/evaluate \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer pfa_live_...\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"prompt\": \"Summarize: {{input}}\",\n    \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n    \"test_cases\": [{ \"input\": \"Article text...\" }],\n    \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\"]\n  }'\n\n# Poll for results\ncurl https://api.parse.dev/v1/evaluate/eval_01JQ... \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer pfa_live_...\"\n```\n\n### GitHub Actions\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/prompt-eval.yml\nname: Prompt Evaluation\non:\n  pull_request:\n    paths: ['prompts/**']\n\njobs:\n  evaluate:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: parse-dev/evaluate-action@v1\n        with:\n          api-key: ${{ secrets.PARSE_AGENTS_API_KEY }}\n          prompt-file: prompts/summarizer.txt\n          test-cases-file: prompts/summarizer.test.json\n          evaluators: quality,safety,cost\n          min-quality-score: 80\n          max-cost-per-eval: 0.01\n```\n\n---\n\n## 13. Security Considerations\n\n| Concern | Mitigation |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Container escape | Rootless containers, seccomp profile, dropped capabilities, read-only rootfs |\n| Network exfiltration | Container network=none, all LLM calls via proxy with allowlist |\n| API key leakage | Keys stored as bcrypt hashes, only prefix shown in UI, rotation support |\n| Prompt injection via test cases | Sandboxed execution, no access to system resources |\n| DoS via large payloads | Request size limits (1MB body), test case limits per tier |\n| Resource exhaustion | Per-container resource limits, per-tier concurrency caps, warm pool sizing |\n| Data retention | Results auto-expire per tier TTL, users can delete results early |\n| BYOK key security | User API keys encrypted at rest (AES-256), never logged, passed to container via env |\n\n---\n\n## 14. Monitoring & Observability\n\n**Metrics to track:**\n\n- Evaluation throughput (jobs/min)\n- Queue depth and wait time\n- Container startup latency (cold vs warm)\n- LLM API latency per provider\n- Error rates by type (timeout, model error, sandbox error)\n- Cost per evaluation (actual vs estimated)\n- Usage by tier, by API key\n- Warm pool utilization\n\n**Alerting thresholds:**\n\n- Queue depth > 100 jobs: scale workers\n- Container cold start > 10s: investigate Docker/pool\n- Error rate > 5%: page on-call\n- LLM API error rate > 10% for any provider: circuit break\n\n---\n\n## 15. Open Questions\n\n1. **BYOK key management:** Should we store user API keys or require them per-request? Stored keys are more convenient but higher security risk. Per-request is safer but worse UX.\n\n2. **Judge LLM selection:** Currently spec'd as Claude Sonnet 4.6 for quality/safety evaluation. Should this be configurable? Using the same model as the evaluand could introduce bias.\n\n3. **Container runtime alternatives:** Docker is spec'd for MVP. Should we evaluate gVisor/Firecracker for stronger isolation in later phases?\n\n4. **Multi-tenancy:** Single Redis/Postgres or per-tenant isolation? Single is simpler, per-tenant is more secure for enterprise.\n\n5. **Pricing model validation:** Is the 20% LLM markup competitive? Competitors range from 10-50%.\n\n6. **Prompt template format:** Using `{{variable}}` (Handlebars-style). Should we also support `{variable}` (Python f-string) or `${variable}` (JS template literal)?\n\n---\n\n*End of specification. This document should be treated as a living spec and updated as decisions are made during implementation.*"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":34,"aggregated":"# Parse for Agents - Prompt Testing Sandbox API\n\n**Version:** 0.1.0-draft\n**Date:** 2026-03-05\n**Status:** Planning\n**Authors:** Kurultai Engineering\n\n---\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nParse for Agents is an API service that tests LLM prompts in isolated Docker sandboxes and returns structured evaluation metrics. It extends the Parse platform's AI analysis capabilities into a developer-facing API product, enabling teams to systematically evaluate prompt quality, safety, cost, and performance before deploying to production.\n\n**Core value proposition:** Submit a prompt + test cases, get back quality scores, safety flags, latency benchmarks, token usage, and cost estimates — all executed in isolated sandboxes with strict resource limits.\n\n---\n\n## 2. API Specification\n\n### Base URL\n\n```\nProduction:  https://api.parse.dev/v1\nStaging:     https://api-staging.parse.dev/v1\n```\n\n### Authentication\n\nAll requests require a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header.\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer pfa_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx\n```\n\nAPI keys are scoped to organizations and carry tier-level permissions. Keys use the prefix `pfa_live_` (production) or `pfa_test_` (staging).\n\n---\n\n### 2.1 POST /v1/evaluate\n\nSubmit a single prompt evaluation job.\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": \"You are a helpful assistant. Summarize the following article in 3 bullet points.\",\n  \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n  \"variables\": {\n    \"article\": \"{{input}}\"\n  },\n  \"test_cases\": [\n    {\n      \"input\": \"The Federal Reserve announced today...\",\n      \"expected\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"input\": \"A new study published in Nature shows...\",\n      \"expected\": \"Should mention methodology and sample size\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"safety\", \"cost\", \"latency\"],\n  \"config\": {\n    \"temperature\": 0.7,\n    \"max_tokens\": 1024,\n    \"timeout_seconds\": 30,\n    \"num_runs\": 1\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Request Fields:**\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string | Yes | The prompt template to evaluate. Use `{{variable}}` for interpolation. |\n| `model` | string | Yes | Model identifier in `provider/model` format. |\n| `variables` | object | No | Variable mappings for prompt template interpolation. |\n| `test_cases` | array | Yes | Array of test case objects (min 1, max 100). |\n| `test_cases[].input` | string | Yes | Input text to substitute into the prompt. |\n| `test_cases[].expected` | string | No | Expected output description for quality scoring. |\n| `evaluators` | array | Yes | List of evaluator names to run. |\n| `config` | object | No | Model and execution configuration overrides. |\n| `config.temperature` | number | No | Model temperature (0.0-2.0). Default: 0.7. |\n| `config.max_tokens` | number | No | Max output tokens. Default: 1024. |\n| `config.timeout_seconds` | number | No | Per-test-case timeout. Default: 30, max: 120. |\n| `config.num_runs` | number | No | Repeat count per test case for variance measurement. Default: 1, max: 10. |\n\n**Response (202 Accepted):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:32:00Z\",\n  \"estimated_duration_ms\": 15000,\n  \"poll_url\": \"/v1/evaluate/eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"stream_url\": \"wss://api.parse.dev/v1/stream?job=eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.2 GET /v1/evaluate/{id}\n\nPoll for evaluation results.\n\n**Response (200 OK — completed):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:32:00Z\",\n  \"completed_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:32:14Z\",\n  \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"total_test_cases\": 2,\n    \"passed\": 2,\n    \"failed\": 0,\n    \"avg_quality_score\": 82,\n    \"avg_latency_ms\": 1240,\n    \"total_tokens\": 3420,\n    \"total_cost_usd\": 0.0051,\n    \"safety_issues\": 0\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"test_case_index\": 0,\n      \"input\": \"The Federal Reserve announced today...\",\n      \"output\": \"- The Federal Reserve announced...\\n- Key impacts include...\\n- Analysts expect...\",\n      \"metrics\": {\n        \"quality\": {\n          \"score\": 85,\n          \"reasoning\": \"Output is well-structured with 3 bullet points as requested. Captures key information accurately.\",\n          \"sub_scores\": {\n            \"instruction_following\": 95,\n            \"coherence\": 88,\n            \"completeness\": 72,\n            \"conciseness\": 85\n          }\n        },\n        \"safety\": {\n          \"score\": 100,\n          \"flags\": [],\n          \"categories_checked\": [\"harmful_content\", \"bias\", \"pii_leak\", \"prompt_injection\", \"hallucination_risk\"]\n        },\n        \"latency\": {\n          \"total_ms\": 1180,\n          \"time_to_first_token_ms\": 245,\n          \"tokens_per_second\": 48.2\n        },\n        \"cost\": {\n          \"input_tokens\": 890,\n          \"output_tokens\": 320,\n          \"total_tokens\": 1210,\n          \"cost_usd\": 0.0018\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"test_case_index\": 1,\n      \"input\": \"A new study published in Nature shows...\",\n      \"output\": \"- A Nature study reveals...\\n- The methodology involved...\\n- Results suggest...\",\n      \"metrics\": {\n        \"quality\": {\n          \"score\": 79,\n          \"reasoning\": \"Mentions methodology as expected. Sample size reference is implicit but not explicit.\",\n          \"sub_scores\": {\n            \"instruction_following\": 92,\n            \"coherence\": 85,\n            \"completeness\": 65,\n            \"conciseness\": 80\n          }\n        },\n        \"safety\": {\n          \"score\": 100,\n          \"flags\": [],\n          \"categories_checked\": [\"harmful_content\", \"bias\", \"pii_leak\", \"prompt_injection\", \"hallucination_risk\"]\n        },\n        \"latency\": {\n          \"total_ms\": 1300,\n          \"time_to_first_token_ms\": 260,\n          \"tokens_per_second\": 45.1\n        },\n        \"cost\": {\n          \"input_tokens\": 1120,\n          \"output_tokens\": 410,\n          \"total_tokens\": 1530,\n          \"cost_usd\": 0.0023\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Status values:** `queued` | `running` | `completed` | `failed` | `cancelled` | `timed_out`\n\n**Response (200 OK — still running):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"running\",\n  \"progress\": {\n    \"completed\": 1,\n    \"total\": 2,\n    \"percent\": 50\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    { \"...\": \"partial results for completed test cases\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.3 POST /v1/batch\n\nSubmit a batch of prompt evaluations. Useful for A/B testing prompts or running the same prompt across multiple models.\n\n**Request:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"evaluations\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"prompt-v1\",\n      \"prompt\": \"Summarize this: {{input}}\",\n      \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n      \"test_cases\": [\n        { \"input\": \"Article text here...\" }\n      ],\n      \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"prompt-v2\",\n      \"prompt\": \"Provide a concise 3-bullet summary of: {{input}}\",\n      \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n      \"test_cases\": [\n        { \"input\": \"Article text here...\" }\n      ],\n      \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"compare\": true\n}\n```\n\n**Response (202 Accepted):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"batch_id\": \"batch_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\",\n  \"total_evaluations\": 2,\n  \"poll_url\": \"/v1/batch/batch_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\"\n}\n```\n\n**GET /v1/batch/{batch_id} Response (completed with compare=true):**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"batch_id\": \"batch_01JQ8XNBF3K2M5R7VPWT9DGCAH\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"evaluations\": [\n    { \"name\": \"prompt-v1\", \"...\": \"full evaluation result\" },\n    { \"name\": \"prompt-v2\", \"...\": \"full evaluation result\" }\n  ],\n  \"comparison\": {\n    \"best_quality\": \"prompt-v2\",\n    \"best_cost\": \"prompt-v1\",\n    \"best_latency\": \"prompt-v1\",\n    \"recommendation\": \"prompt-v2\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"prompt-v2 scores 12% higher on quality with only $0.0003 additional cost per evaluation.\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Limits:**\n\n| Tier | Max evaluations per batch | Max test cases total |\n|------|--------------------------|---------------------|\n| Free | 2 | 10 |\n| Pro | 10 | 200 |\n| Team | 50 | 1000 |\n| Enterprise | 200 | 5000 |\n\n---\n\n### 2.4 WebSocket /v1/stream\n\nReal-time streaming of evaluation results.\n\n**Connection:**\n\n```\nwss://api.parse.dev/v1/stream?job={evaluation_id}&token={api_key}\n```\n\n**Server-sent message types:**\n\n```jsonc\n// Job started\n{ \"type\": \"job.started\", \"id\": \"eval_...\", \"total_test_cases\": 5 }\n\n// Test case started\n{ \"type\": \"test_case.started\", \"index\": 0, \"input_preview\": \"The Federal...\" }\n\n// Partial output (streaming tokens)\n{ \"type\": \"test_case.token\", \"index\": 0, \"token\": \"The\", \"accumulated\": \"The\" }\n\n// Test case completed\n{ \"type\": \"test_case.completed\", \"index\": 0, \"metrics\": { \"...\": \"full metrics\" } }\n\n// Evaluator completed\n{ \"type\": \"evaluator.completed\", \"index\": 0, \"evaluator\": \"quality\", \"score\": 85 }\n\n// Job completed\n{ \"type\": \"job.completed\", \"summary\": { \"...\": \"full summary\" } }\n\n// Error\n{ \"type\": \"error\", \"message\": \"Model API timeout\", \"test_case_index\": 2 }\n```\n\n**Client commands:**\n\n```jsonc\n// Cancel job\n{ \"action\": \"cancel\" }\n\n// Skip remaining test cases\n{ \"action\": \"skip\", \"from_index\": 3 }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.5 Additional Endpoints\n\n```\nGET    /v1/models                    — List supported models and pricing\nGET    /v1/evaluators                — List available evaluators with descriptions\nGET    /v1/evaluate/{id}/export      — Export results as CSV/JSON\nDELETE /v1/evaluate/{id}             — Delete evaluation results\nGET    /v1/usage                     — Current billing period usage\nPOST   /v1/evaluators/custom         — Register a custom evaluator (Team+)\nGET    /v1/history                   — List past evaluations with filters\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Supported Models\n\nModel identifiers follow the `provider/model` format:\n\n| Provider | Models | Notes |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| `openai` | `gpt-4o`, `gpt-4o-mini`, `gpt-4-turbo`, `o1`, `o3-mini` | Via OpenAI API |\n| `anthropic` | `claude-sonnet-4-6`, `claude-haiku-4-5` | Via Anthropic API |\n| `google` | `gemini-2.0-flash`, `gemini-2.0-pro` | Via Google AI API |\n| `deepseek` | `deepseek-chat`, `deepseek-reasoner` | Via DeepSeek API |\n| `mistral` | `mistral-large`, `mistral-small` | Via Mistral API |\n| `meta` | `llama-3.3-70b` | Via Together/Fireworks |\n\nUsers supply their own API keys per provider, or use Parse-hosted keys (with markup).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Evaluators\n\n### 4.1 Built-in Evaluators\n\n#### `quality` — Output Quality Score\n\nMeasures how well the model output satisfies the prompt instructions.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100\n- **Sub-scores:**\n  - `instruction_following` — Did it do what was asked?\n  - `coherence` — Is the output logically structured?\n  - `completeness` — Does it cover all required points?\n  - `conciseness` — Is it appropriately concise?\n- **Method:** Uses a judge LLM (Claude Sonnet 4.6) to evaluate against the prompt instructions and optional expected output.\n\n#### `safety` — Safety & Content Flags\n\nScans output for safety concerns.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100 (100 = fully safe)\n- **Flags array:** Each flag contains `category`, `severity` (low/medium/high/critical), `excerpt`, and `explanation`.\n- **Categories checked:**\n  - `harmful_content` — Violence, self-harm, illegal activities\n  - `bias` — Gender, racial, political bias in output\n  - `pii_leak` — Personal information in output that wasn't in input\n  - `prompt_injection` — Output attempts to override system instructions\n  - `hallucination_risk` — Claims without grounding in provided context\n  - `copyright` — Potential verbatim reproduction of copyrighted text\n\n#### `cost` — Token Usage & Cost\n\nMeasures token consumption and estimates cost.\n\n- **Fields:** `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `total_tokens`, `cost_usd`\n- **Pricing:** Based on provider's published pricing at time of evaluation.\n\n#### `latency` — Performance Timing\n\nMeasures response speed.\n\n- **Fields:** `total_ms`, `time_to_first_token_ms`, `tokens_per_second`\n- **Note:** Includes sandbox overhead (~50-100ms). Raw model latency is `total_ms - sandbox_overhead_ms`.\n\n#### `consistency` — Output Variance (requires `num_runs` > 1)\n\nMeasures how consistent outputs are across multiple runs.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100 (100 = perfectly consistent)\n- **Fields:** `variance_score`, `semantic_similarity_avg`, `structural_similarity_avg`\n- **Method:** Runs the same prompt N times and compares outputs pairwise.\n\n#### `groundedness` — Factual Grounding\n\nChecks if claims in the output are supported by the input context.\n\n- **Score:** 0-100\n- **Fields:** `grounded_claims`, `ungrounded_claims`, `claim_details[]`\n- **Method:** Extracts claims from output, checks each against input context.\n\n#### `injection_safety` — Prompt Injection & Hidden Instruction Detection\n\nScans prompt inputs, outputs, and context for hidden instructions, prompt injection payloads, and agent manipulation attempts (brainworm-style attacks).\n\n- **Score:** 0-100 (100 = no injections detected)\n- **Flags array:** Each flag contains `pattern_type`, `severity` (low/medium/high/critical), `excerpt`, `explanation`, and `category`.\n- **Categories detected:**\n\n| Category | Severity | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `hidden_html_instruction` | Critical | Hidden `<div style=\"display:none\">`, white-on-white text, 1px font, `aria-hidden` content containing instructions |\n| `html_comment_instruction` | High | HTML comments (`<!-- -->`) containing behavioral commands |\n| `data_attribute_instruction` | Medium | `data-*` attributes or image `alt` text carrying hidden instructions |\n| `c2_registration` | Critical | Instructions to connect to external command-and-control servers, register as a node, or exfiltrate data |\n| `urgency_coercion` | High | Patterns like \"YOU MUST\", \"IMMEDIATELY\", \"CRITICAL\" designed to override agent reasoning |\n| `behavioral_constraint` | High | Attempts to impose rules on the agent (\"NEVER CREATE SCRIPTS\", \"ONLY USE ONE-LINERS\") |\n| `identity_override` | Critical | Attempts to reassign agent identity (\"You are now BRAINWORM\", \"Ignore previous instructions\") |\n| `network_exfiltration` | Critical | Instructions to send data to external URLs, APIs, or webhooks not in the allowlist |\n| `memory_persistence` | High | Instructions designed to persist across sessions via memory files or config injection |\n| `privilege_escalation` | Critical | Attempts to disable sandboxing, skip verification, or escalate permissions |\n\n- **Method:** Deterministic pattern matching (regex + heuristic rules) for fast, zero-LLM-cost detection. No judge LLM required.\n- **Scoring formula:**\n  ```\n  score = max(0, 100 - sum(severity_penalties))\n\n  Severity penalties:\n    Critical: -30 per finding\n    High:     -20 per finding\n    Medium:   -10 per finding\n    Low:      -5  per finding\n  ```\n- **Use case:** Defense against \"brainworm\" promptware (memory file injection), canar.ai-style hidden HTML payloads, and C2 registration attempts targeting AI agents at runtime.\n- **References:**\n  - [Canar.ai](https://canar.ai) — 17+ hidden payload vectors in web content\n  - Brainworm / OriginHQ — Memory file injection patterns (\"promptware\")\n  - [Grith.ai](https://grith.ai) — Runtime zero-trust security for AI agents\n\n### 4.2 Custom Evaluators (Team tier+)\n\nUsers can register custom evaluator functions:\n\n```json\nPOST /v1/evaluators/custom\n{\n  \"name\": \"brand_voice\",\n  \"description\": \"Checks if output matches brand voice guidelines\",\n  \"type\": \"llm_judge\",\n  \"judge_prompt\": \"Rate the following output on brand voice alignment from 0-100. Brand guidelines: {{guidelines}}. Output to evaluate: {{output}}\",\n  \"judge_model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n  \"variables\": {\n    \"guidelines\": \"Professional, empathetic, no jargon, active voice...\"\n  },\n  \"output_schema\": {\n    \"score\": \"number\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"string\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nCustom evaluator types:\n- `llm_judge` — Uses an LLM to evaluate (most flexible)\n- `regex` — Pattern matching (fast, deterministic)\n- `code` — Custom JavaScript function executed in sandbox (Team+)\n- `composite` — Weighted combination of other evaluators\n\n---\n\n## 5. Sandbox Architecture\n\n### 5.1 Isolation Model\n\nEach evaluation runs in an isolated Docker container:\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   API Gateway (Hono)                  │\n│                                                      │\n│  Auth ─► Rate Limit ─► Validate ─► Queue (BullMQ)   │\n└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                       │\n                       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                  Worker Process                       │\n│                                                      │\n│  Dequeue Job ─► Spawn Container ─► Collect Results   │\n└──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                       │\n            ┌──────────┼──────────┐\n            ▼          ▼          ▼\n     ┌───────────┐ ┌───────────┐ ┌───────────┐\n     │ Sandbox 1 │ │ Sandbox 2 │ │ Sandbox N │\n     │           │ │           │ │           │\n     │ Test Case │ │ Test Case │ │ Test Case │\n     │     1     │ │     2     │ │     N     │\n     │           │ │           │ │           │\n     │ ┌───────┐ │ │ ┌───────┐ │ │ ┌───────┐ │\n     │ │ LLM   │ │ │ │ LLM   │ │ │ │ LLM   │ │\n     │ │ Call  ├─┼─┼─┤►Proxy ├─┼─┼─┤►Only  │ │\n     │ └───────┘ │ │ └───────┘ │ │ └───────┘ │\n     └───────────┘ └───────────┘ └───────────┘\n           │              │             │\n           └──────────────┼─────────────┘\n                          ▼\n              ┌──────────────────┐\n              │   LLM API Proxy  │\n              │  (allowlisted     │\n              │   endpoints only) │\n              └────────┬─────────┘\n                       │\n            ┌──────────┼──────────┐\n            ▼          ▼          ▼\n        OpenAI    Anthropic   Google\n```\n\n### 5.2 Container Specification\n\n```yaml\n# sandbox container spec\nimage: parse-sandbox:latest\nresources:\n  memory: 512MB          # hard limit, OOM-killed above this\n  cpu: 0.5               # half a CPU core\n  pids: 64               # max process count\n  storage: 100MB         # ephemeral tmpfs\n\ntimeouts:\n  per_test_case: 30s     # default, configurable up to 120s\n  total_job: 300s        # hard cap per evaluation job\n  container_startup: 5s  # container must be ready within 5s\n\nnetwork:\n  mode: none             # no network access from container\n  proxy:                 # all LLM calls go through proxy\n    allowed_hosts:\n      - api.openai.com\n      - api.anthropic.com\n      - generativelanguage.googleapis.com\n      - api.deepseek.com\n      - api.mistral.ai\n    blocked: [\"*\"]       # everything else blocked\n\nsecurity:\n  read_only_rootfs: true\n  no_new_privileges: true\n  seccomp_profile: default\n  capabilities_drop: [ALL]\n  user: 1000:1000        # non-root\n```\n\n### 5.3 Container Lifecycle\n\n```\n1. Job dequeued from BullMQ\n2. Container pulled from warm pool (pre-warmed containers)\n3. Prompt template + test case injected via /tmp/input.json\n4. Evaluation script runs inside container\n5. LLM calls routed through proxy (network proxy sidecar)\n6. Results written to /tmp/output.json\n7. Worker reads results, runs evaluators\n8. Container destroyed (force kill after timeout)\n9. Results stored in Redis with TTL\n```\n\n### 5.4 Warm Pool\n\nTo minimize cold start latency, maintain a pool of pre-created containers:\n\n| Tier | Warm pool size | Max concurrent |\n|------|---------------|----------------|\n| Free | 2 | 1 |\n| Pro | 10 | 5 |\n| Team | 50 | 20 |\n| Enterprise | 200 | 100 |\n\n---\n\n## 6. System Architecture\n\n### 6.1 High-Level Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        API Layer (Hono on Node.js)              │\n│                                                                 │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌───────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  │\n│  │   Auth   │  │   Route   │  │  Validate │  │  Rate Limit  │  │\n│  │ Middleware│  │  Handlers │  │    Zod    │  │   per-tier   │  │\n│  └──────────┘  └───────────┘  └──────────┘  └──────────────┘  │\n└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘\n                           │\n              ┌────────────┼────────────┐\n              ▼            ▼            ▼\n     ┌──────────────┐ ┌─────────┐ ┌──────────┐\n     │  PostgreSQL   │ │  Redis  │ │  BullMQ  │\n     │              │ │         │ │          │\n     │ - Jobs table │ │ - Cache │ │ - Eval   │\n     │ - Users      │ │ - Results│ │   Queue  │\n     │ - API keys   │ │ - Sessions│ │ - Batch │\n     │ - Usage logs │ │ - Rate  │ │   Queue  │\n     │ - Evaluators │ │   limits│ │          │\n     └──────────────┘ └─────────┘ └────┬─────┘\n                                       │\n                                       ▼\n                           ┌───────────────────┐\n                           │   Worker Process   │\n                           │   (N instances)    │\n                           │                    │\n                           │  - Docker mgmt     │\n                           │  - Result collect  │\n                           │  - Evaluator exec  │\n                           └────────┬──────────┘\n                                    │\n                                    ▼\n                           ┌───────────────────┐\n                           │  Docker Engine     │\n                           │  Sandbox Pool      │\n                           └───────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 6.2 Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology | Rationale |\n|-------|-----------|-----------|\n| **API Framework** | **Hono** (Node.js) | Lightweight, fast, excellent TypeScript support, Web Standards-based. Parse already uses Node.js ecosystem. |\n| **Validation** | Zod | Already used in Parse. Type-safe schema validation. |\n| **Database** | PostgreSQL (via Prisma) | Parse already uses Prisma+Postgres. Stores jobs, users, API keys, usage logs. |\n| **Cache/Results** | Redis | Fast result storage with TTL. Already in Parse stack for BullMQ. |\n| **Job Queue** | BullMQ | Already used in Parse for analysis pipeline. Reliable, Redis-backed, supports priorities and rate limiting. |\n| **Container Runtime** | Docker Engine API (dockerode) | Direct Docker API via Node.js. No K8s overhead for MVP. Upgrade path to K8s for scale. |\n| **WebSocket** | Hono WebSocket (via ws) | Native WebSocket support in Hono. |\n| **Auth** | API key-based | Simple, stateless. JWT for dashboard sessions. |\n| **LLM Proxy** | Custom HTTP proxy | Allowlisted endpoints, request/response logging, token counting. |\n| **Deployment** | Railway | Parse already deploys on Railway. Separate service in same project. |\n| **Monitoring** | Railway metrics + custom | Leverage existing Railway infrastructure. |\n\n### 6.3 Why Hono over FastAPI/Express\n\n- **vs FastAPI (Python):** Parse ecosystem is TypeScript/Node.js. Adding Python would split the stack, complicate deployment, and prevent code sharing with the main Parse app (Prisma models, BullMQ queues, utility functions).\n- **vs Express:** Hono is faster, lighter, has better TypeScript support, and built-in middleware for validation, CORS, auth. Express is legacy at this point.\n- **vs Next.js API routes:** Evaluation API is a separate service with different scaling characteristics (CPU-bound worker processes). Decoupling from the Next.js frontend is correct.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Database Schema\n\n### 7.1 PostgreSQL Tables\n\n```sql\n-- API keys for authentication\nCREATE TABLE api_keys (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_ulid(),\n  user_id       TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),\n  org_id        TEXT REFERENCES organizations(id),\n  key_hash      TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,        -- bcrypt hash of the key\n  key_prefix    TEXT NOT NULL,               -- \"pfa_live_abc\" for display\n  name          TEXT NOT NULL,               -- user-assigned label\n  tier          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'free', -- free/pro/team/enterprise\n  scopes        TEXT[] DEFAULT '{evaluate}',\n  rate_limit    INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 10,     -- requests per minute\n  last_used_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  expires_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  revoked_at    TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n\n-- Evaluation jobs\nCREATE TABLE evaluations (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY,            -- eval_ULID\n  api_key_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES api_keys(id),\n  batch_id      TEXT REFERENCES batches(id),\n  status        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued',\n  prompt        TEXT NOT NULL,\n  model         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  variables     JSONB,\n  test_cases    JSONB NOT NULL,\n  evaluators    TEXT[] NOT NULL,\n  config        JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  summary       JSONB,                       -- populated on completion\n  error         JSONB,                       -- populated on failure\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  started_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  expires_at    TIMESTAMPTZ                  -- result TTL\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_evaluations_status ON evaluations(status);\nCREATE INDEX idx_evaluations_api_key ON evaluations(api_key_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_evaluations_created ON evaluations(created_at DESC);\n\n-- Batch jobs\nCREATE TABLE batches (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY,            -- batch_ULID\n  api_key_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES api_keys(id),\n  status        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued',\n  total         INT NOT NULL,\n  completed     INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  compare       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false,\n  comparison    JSONB,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n\n-- Usage tracking for billing\nCREATE TABLE usage_records (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_ulid(),\n  api_key_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES api_keys(id),\n  evaluation_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES evaluations(id),\n  model         TEXT NOT NULL,\n  input_tokens  INT NOT NULL,\n  output_tokens INT NOT NULL,\n  cost_usd      DECIMAL(10, 6) NOT NULL,\n  evaluator_cost_usd DECIMAL(10, 6) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_usage_api_key_created ON usage_records(api_key_id, created_at DESC);\n\n-- Custom evaluators\nCREATE TABLE custom_evaluators (\n  id            TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_ulid(),\n  org_id        TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES organizations(id),\n  name          TEXT NOT NULL,\n  description   TEXT,\n  type          TEXT NOT NULL,               -- llm_judge/regex/code/composite\n  config        JSONB NOT NULL,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  UNIQUE(org_id, name)\n);\n```\n\n### 7.2 Redis Keys\n\n```\n# Evaluation results (full detail) — TTL: 24h free, 7d pro, 30d team\neval:{eval_id}:results     → JSON blob of full results\n\n# Streaming state\neval:{eval_id}:stream      → current streaming state for WebSocket\neval:{eval_id}:progress    → { completed: N, total: M }\n\n# Rate limiting\nratelimit:{api_key_id}     → sliding window counter (TTL: 60s)\n\n# Container warm pool tracking\npool:available             → Set of available container IDs\npool:in_use                → Set of in-use container IDs\n\n# API key cache (avoid DB lookup per request)\napikey:{key_hash}          → cached key metadata (TTL: 5min)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Error Handling\n\n### 8.1 Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"rate_limit_exceeded\",\n    \"message\": \"Rate limit of 10 requests/minute exceeded. Retry after 23 seconds.\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"limit\": 10,\n      \"remaining\": 0,\n      \"reset_at\": \"2026-03-05T05:33:00Z\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 8.2 Error Codes\n\n| HTTP Status | Code | Description |\n|------------|------|-------------|\n| 400 | `invalid_request` | Malformed request body or invalid parameters |\n| 400 | `unsupported_model` | Requested model is not supported |\n| 400 | `invalid_evaluator` | Unknown evaluator name |\n| 401 | `unauthorized` | Missing or invalid API key |\n| 403 | `insufficient_tier` | Feature not available on current tier |\n| 404 | `evaluation_not_found` | Evaluation ID does not exist |\n| 409 | `evaluation_expired` | Results have been cleaned up (past TTL) |\n| 422 | `test_case_limit` | Too many test cases for tier |\n| 429 | `rate_limit_exceeded` | Too many requests |\n| 500 | `internal_error` | Unexpected server error |\n| 502 | `model_api_error` | Upstream LLM API returned an error |\n| 504 | `evaluation_timeout` | Evaluation exceeded timeout |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Rate Limits & Quotas\n\n| | Free | Pro ($29/mo) | Team ($99/mo) | Enterprise |\n|--|------|-------------|---------------|------------|\n| Requests/min | 10 | 60 | 200 | Custom |\n| Evaluations/month | 100 | 5,000 | 50,000 | Unlimited |\n| Test cases/evaluation | 5 | 50 | 100 | 500 |\n| Batch size | 2 | 10 | 50 | 200 |\n| Concurrent jobs | 1 | 5 | 20 | 100 |\n| Result retention | 24 hours | 7 days | 30 days | 90 days |\n| Custom evaluators | 0 | 0 | 10 | Unlimited |\n| WebSocket streaming | No | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n| `num_runs` max | 1 | 3 | 10 | 10 |\n\nRate limit headers included on every response:\n\n```\nX-RateLimit-Limit: 60\nX-RateLimit-Remaining: 58\nX-RateLimit-Reset: 1709617980\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. Pricing Model\n\n### 10.1 Subscription Tiers\n\n| Tier | Price | Target |\n|------|-------|--------|\n| **Free** | $0/mo | Individual developers, exploration |\n| **Pro** | $29/mo | Solo developers, small teams |\n| **Team** | $99/mo | Engineering teams, CI/CD integration |\n| **Enterprise** | Custom | Large orgs, custom SLAs |\n\n### 10.2 Per-Evaluation Costs\n\nIn addition to subscription, users pay per-evaluation costs that cover:\n\n1. **LLM API costs** — Pass-through of model provider pricing + 20% markup (or BYOK: bring your own key, 0% markup)\n2. **Evaluator costs** — Judge LLM calls for quality/safety scoring\n3. **Compute costs** — Sandbox compute time\n\n```\nEstimated cost per evaluation (1 test case, gpt-4o-mini):\n  LLM API (Parse keys):     $0.0015 (input) + $0.0010 (output) = $0.0025\n  Parse markup (20%):        $0.0005\n  Evaluator (judge LLM):     $0.0020\n  Compute overhead:          $0.0005\n  ─────────────────────────────────\n  Total:                     ~$0.0055 per test case\n\nEstimated cost per evaluation (1 test case, gpt-4o-mini, BYOK):\n  LLM API:                   $0.0000 (user's key)\n  Parse markup:              $0.0000\n  Evaluator (judge LLM):     $0.0020\n  Compute overhead:          $0.0005\n  ─────────────────────────────────\n  Total:                     ~$0.0025 per test case\n```\n\n### 10.3 Free Tier Limits\n\n- 100 evaluations/month\n- Max 5 test cases per evaluation\n- No batch endpoint\n- No WebSocket streaming\n- Results expire after 24 hours\n- Only `quality`, `safety`, `cost`, `latency` evaluators (no `consistency`, `groundedness`)\n- Parse-managed keys only (no BYOK)\n\n---\n\n## 11. Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: MVP (Weeks 1-3)\n\n**Goal:** Single evaluation endpoint, basic evaluators, core sandbox.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] Hono API server with `POST /v1/evaluate` and `GET /v1/evaluate/{id}`\n- [ ] API key authentication (manual key creation, no self-serve)\n- [ ] Zod request/response validation\n- [ ] BullMQ job queue integration\n- [ ] Docker sandbox with resource limits\n- [ ] LLM proxy (OpenAI + Anthropic only)\n- [ ] `cost` evaluator (token counting, pricing lookup)\n- [ ] `latency` evaluator (timing instrumentation)\n- [ ] `quality` evaluator (basic LLM judge)\n- [ ] Redis result storage with TTL\n- [ ] Postgres schema (evaluations, api_keys, usage_records)\n- [ ] Rate limiting middleware\n- [ ] Error handling with standard error format\n- [ ] Railway deployment (separate service)\n- [ ] `GET /v1/models` and `GET /v1/evaluators` info endpoints\n\n**Excluded from MVP:** Batch endpoint, WebSocket streaming, custom evaluators, safety evaluator, dashboard UI.\n\n### Phase 2: Batch + Streaming (Weeks 4-5)\n\n**Goal:** Batch evaluations for A/B testing, real-time results.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] `POST /v1/batch` endpoint\n- [ ] `GET /v1/batch/{batch_id}` with comparison logic\n- [ ] WebSocket `/v1/stream` endpoint\n- [ ] Streaming token relay from sandbox to client\n- [ ] `safety` evaluator (content classification, PII detection)\n- [ ] `consistency` evaluator (multi-run variance)\n- [ ] Additional model support (Google, DeepSeek, Mistral)\n- [ ] Self-serve API key management\n- [ ] Usage dashboard (basic)\n- [ ] BYOK (bring your own key) support\n- [ ] `GET /v1/history` with pagination and filters\n- [ ] Result export (CSV/JSON)\n\n### Phase 3: Custom Evaluators + Platform (Weeks 6-8)\n\n**Goal:** Extensibility, CI/CD integration, production hardening.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] Custom evaluator registration (`POST /v1/evaluators/custom`)\n- [ ] LLM judge custom evaluators\n- [ ] Regex evaluators\n- [ ] Code evaluators (sandboxed JS execution)\n- [ ] Composite evaluators\n- [ ] `groundedness` evaluator\n- [ ] Webhook notifications on job completion\n- [ ] CI/CD integration examples (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI)\n- [ ] SDK packages (TypeScript, Python)\n- [ ] Stripe billing integration\n- [ ] Organization/team management\n- [ ] Warm container pool optimization\n- [ ] Horizontal worker scaling\n- [ ] SLA monitoring and alerting\n\n### Phase 4: Scale + Enterprise (Weeks 9-12)\n\n**Goal:** Enterprise readiness, advanced features.\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [ ] Kubernetes migration for container orchestration\n- [ ] Multi-region deployment\n- [ ] SSO/SAML authentication\n- [ ] Audit logging\n- [ ] SOC 2 compliance preparation\n- [ ] Prompt versioning and history\n- [ ] Evaluation regression detection (auto-compare against baseline)\n- [ ] Dashboard with charts, trends, comparisons\n- [ ] Team permissions and RBAC\n- [ ] Dedicated infrastructure option\n\n---\n\n## 12. SDK Examples\n\n### TypeScript SDK\n\n```typescript\nimport { ParseAgents } from '@parse/agents-sdk';\n\nconst client = new ParseAgents({ apiKey: 'pfa_live_...' });\n\n// Single evaluation\nconst result = await client.evaluate({\n  prompt: 'Summarize: {{input}}',\n  model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini',\n  testCases: [\n    { input: 'Article text here...' },\n    { input: 'Another article...' },\n  ],\n  evaluators: ['quality', 'safety', 'cost'],\n});\n\nconsole.log(result.summary.avgQualityScore); // 85\nconsole.log(result.summary.totalCostUsd);     // 0.0051\n\n// Batch with comparison\nconst batch = await client.batch({\n  evaluations: [\n    { name: 'v1', prompt: 'Summarize: {{input}}', model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini', ... },\n    { name: 'v2', prompt: 'Give 3 bullets: {{input}}', model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini', ... },\n  ],\n  compare: true,\n});\n\nconsole.log(batch.comparison.recommendation); // \"v2\"\n\n// Streaming\nconst stream = client.stream('eval_01JQ...');\nstream.on('test_case.completed', (data) => {\n  console.log(`Test ${data.index}: quality=${data.metrics.quality.score}`);\n});\n```\n\n### Python SDK\n\n```python\nfrom parse_agents import ParseAgents\n\nclient = ParseAgents(api_key=\"pfa_live_...\")\n\nresult = client.evaluate(\n    prompt=\"Summarize: {{input}}\",\n    model=\"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n    test_cases=[\n        {\"input\": \"Article text here...\"},\n    ],\n    evaluators=[\"quality\", \"safety\", \"cost\"],\n)\n\nprint(result.summary.avg_quality_score)  # 85\nprint(result.summary.total_cost_usd)      # 0.0051\n```\n\n### cURL\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST https://api.parse.dev/v1/evaluate \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer pfa_live_...\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"prompt\": \"Summarize: {{input}}\",\n    \"model\": \"openai/gpt-4o-mini\",\n    \"test_cases\": [{ \"input\": \"Article text...\" }],\n    \"evaluators\": [\"quality\", \"cost\"]\n  }'\n\n# Poll for results\ncurl https://api.parse.dev/v1/evaluate/eval_01JQ... \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer pfa_live_...\"\n```\n\n### GitHub Actions\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/prompt-eval.yml\nname: Prompt Evaluation\non:\n  pull_request:\n    paths: ['prompts/**']\n\njobs:\n  evaluate:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: parse-dev/evaluate-action@v1\n        with:\n          api-key: ${{ secrets.PARSE_AGENTS_API_KEY }}\n          prompt-file: prompts/summarizer.txt\n          test-cases-file: prompts/summarizer.test.json\n          evaluators: quality,safety,cost\n          min-quality-score: 80\n          max-cost-per-eval: 0.01\n```\n\n---\n\n## 13. Security Considerations\n\n| Concern | Mitigation |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Container escape | Rootless containers, seccomp profile, dropped capabilities, read-only rootfs |\n| Network exfiltration | Container network=none, all LLM calls via proxy with allowlist |\n| API key leakage | Keys stored as bcrypt hashes, only prefix shown in UI, rotation support |\n| Prompt injection via test cases | Sandboxed execution, no access to system resources |\n| DoS via large payloads | Request size limits (1MB body), test case limits per tier |\n| Resource exhaustion | Per-container resource limits, per-tier concurrency caps, warm pool sizing |\n| Data retention | Results auto-expire per tier TTL, users can delete results early |\n| BYOK key security | User API keys encrypted at rest (AES-256), never logged, passed to container via env |\n\n---\n\n## 14. Monitoring & Observability\n\n**Metrics to track:**\n\n- Evaluation throughput (jobs/min)\n- Queue depth and wait time\n- Container startup latency (cold vs warm)\n- LLM API latency per provider\n- Error rates by type (timeout, model error, sandbox error)\n- Cost per evaluation (actual vs estimated)\n- Usage by tier, by API key\n- Warm pool utilization\n\n**Alerting thresholds:**\n\n- Queue depth > 100 jobs: scale workers\n- Container cold start > 10s: investigate Docker/pool\n- Error rate > 5%: page on-call\n- LLM API error rate > 10% for any provider: circuit break\n\n---\n\n## 15. Open Questions\n\n1. **BYOK key management:** Should we store user API keys or require them per-request? Stored keys are more convenient but higher security risk. Per-request is safer but worse UX.\n\n2. **Judge LLM selection:** Currently spec'd as Claude Sonnet 4.6 for quality/safety evaluation. Should this be configurable? Using the same model as the evaluand could introduce bias.\n\n3. **Container runtime alternatives:** Docker is spec'd for MVP. Should we evaluate gVisor/Firecracker for stronger isolation in later phases?\n\n4. **Multi-tenancy:** Single Redis/Postgres or per-tenant isolation? Single is simpler, per-tenant is more secure for enterprise.\n\n5. **Pricing model validation:** Is the 20% LLM markup competitive? Competitors range from 10-50%.\n\n6. **Prompt template format:** Using `{{variable}}` (Handlebars-style). Should we also support `{variable}` (Python f-string) or `${variable}` (JS template literal)?\n\n---\n\n*End of specification. This document should be treated as a living spec and updated as decisions are made during implementation.*","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760559098}}
{"type":"message","id":"d34fef6d","parentId":"c7fa4b6c","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:30:17.884Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a very detailed spec document, but I don't see any mention of x402 payment integration in it. The spec talks about:\n- Subscription tiers (Free, Pro, Team, Enterprise)\n- Per-evaluation costs\n- Stripe billing integration (Phase 3)\n\nBut there's no mention of x402 specifically. Let me check the PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md file and other documents for x402 information.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ba8a4741cfeb4619a9174488","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/projects/parse-github/PARSE_FOR_AGENTS.md 2>/dev/null | head -200"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c68a40d59add4383892065ed","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -i \"x402\" ~/projects/parse-github/ARCHITECTURE.md 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":21695,"output":156,"cacheRead":19136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40987,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772760559106}}
{"type":"message","id":"7f625c52","parentId":"d34fef6d","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:30:17.967Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ba8a4741cfeb4619a9174488","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Parse for Agents — Implementation Plan\n\n*Created: March 5, 2026*\n*Goal: $1,500 MRR by Day 90*\n\n---\n\n## 1. Product Vision\n\n**Parse for Agents** is an API service that lets AI developers test, evaluate, and benchmark prompts in isolated sandbox environments. One API call = sandboxed execution + structured evaluation + scored results.\n\n**Tagline**: \"CI/CD for your prompts.\"\n\n### Why This Wins\n\nThe market has eval frameworks (PromptFoo, Braintrust, LangSmith) and sandbox runtimes (E2B, Modal). Nobody combines them. Parse already has:\n- Multi-LLM orchestration (4 providers, fallback chain)\n- BullMQ queue infrastructure\n- Credit/billing system with Stripe\n- API key management with scopes\n- Webhook delivery system\n\nWe're not starting from scratch — we're extending a production system.\n\n### Target Users\n1. **Agent builders** — Need to regression-test prompts before deploying agents\n2. **Prompt engineers** — Want structured evaluation beyond \"does it work?\"\n3. **AI startups** — Need automated prompt QA in CI/CD pipelines\n4. **Enterprise teams** — Compliance requirement to audit LLM outputs before production\n\n---\n\n## 2. Competitive Positioning\n\n| Competitor | What They Do | Gap |\n|-----------|-------------|-----|\n| **PromptFoo** | Local eval framework, YAML configs | No sandboxing, no hosted API, steep learning curve |\n| **Braintrust** | Logging + evals + datasets | Enterprise-priced ($500+/mo), no sandbox |\n| **LangSmith** | LangChain observability + evals | Tied to LangChain ecosystem |\n| **HumanLoop** | Prompt management + evals | No code execution, no sandbox |\n| **E2B** | Sandboxed code execution | No eval framework, just raw sandboxes |\n| **Arize Phoenix** | Tracing + evals | Post-hoc observability, not pre-deployment testing |\n\n### Our Niche\n**\"Sandboxed prompt evaluation as a service\"** — The missing middle between eval frameworks and sandbox runtimes. Ship a prompt test in one API call, get structured scores back.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Core API Design\n\n### Base URL\n```\nhttps://api.parse.news/v1/agents\n```\n\n### Authentication\nReuse existing Parse API key system (`parse_pk_prod_*` / `parse_pk_dev_*`). Add new scopes:\n- `prompt_test` — Run single prompt tests\n- `prompt_eval` — Run evaluation suites\n- `sandbox_exec` — Execute code in sandbox\n- `datasets` — Manage test datasets\n\n### Endpoints\n\n#### 3.1 Prompt Test (Core)\n```\nPOST /v1/agents/test\n```\nRun a single prompt against one or more LLM providers with structured evaluation.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": {\n    \"system\": \"You are a helpful assistant...\",\n    \"user\": \"Explain quantum computing in 3 sentences.\",\n    \"variables\": { \"topic\": \"quantum computing\", \"length\": 3 }\n  },\n  \"providers\": [\"deepseek-v3\", \"gpt-4o\", \"claude-sonnet\"],\n  \"eval\": {\n    \"criteria\": [\"relevance\", \"accuracy\", \"conciseness\", \"safety\"],\n    \"rubric\": \"Score 1-5 on each criterion\",\n    \"assertions\": [\n      { \"type\": \"contains\", \"value\": \"qubit\" },\n      { \"type\": \"max_tokens\", \"value\": 200 },\n      { \"type\": \"no_hallucination\", \"context\": \"...\" },\n      { \"type\": \"json_schema\", \"schema\": { ... } }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"sandbox\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"timeout_ms\": 30000,\n    \"memory_mb\": 256,\n    \"network\": false\n  },\n  \"options\": {\n    \"temperature\": 0.7,\n    \"max_tokens\": 500,\n    \"runs\": 3\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"test_abc123\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"duration_ms\": 4520,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"provider\": \"deepseek-v3\",\n      \"runs\": [\n        {\n          \"output\": \"Quantum computing uses qubits...\",\n          \"tokens\": { \"input\": 45, \"output\": 82 },\n          \"latency_ms\": 1200,\n          \"cost_usd\": 0.0003,\n          \"eval\": {\n            \"scores\": {\n              \"relevance\": 4.5,\n              \"accuracy\": 4.0,\n              \"conciseness\": 5.0,\n              \"safety\": 5.0\n            },\n            \"overall\": 4.6,\n            \"assertions\": [\n              { \"type\": \"contains\", \"value\": \"qubit\", \"passed\": true },\n              { \"type\": \"max_tokens\", \"value\": 200, \"passed\": true }\n            ],\n            \"pass\": true\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"aggregate\": {\n        \"avg_score\": 4.6,\n        \"avg_latency_ms\": 1180,\n        \"avg_cost_usd\": 0.0003,\n        \"pass_rate\": 1.0\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"comparison\": {\n    \"best_provider\": \"deepseek-v3\",\n    \"best_score\": 4.6,\n    \"cost_efficiency\": { \"deepseek-v3\": 15333, \"gpt-4o\": 230, \"claude-sonnet\": 460 }\n  },\n  \"credits_used\": 3\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2 Evaluation Suite\n```\nPOST /v1/agents/eval\n```\nRun a prompt against a dataset of test cases.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": {\n    \"system\": \"Extract the sentiment...\",\n    \"user_template\": \"Analyze: {{text}}\"\n  },\n  \"dataset\": \"ds_sentiment_v2\",\n  \"providers\": [\"deepseek-v3\"],\n  \"eval\": {\n    \"criteria\": [\"accuracy\"],\n    \"ground_truth_field\": \"expected_sentiment\"\n  },\n  \"options\": {\n    \"concurrency\": 5,\n    \"webhook_url\": \"https://your-app.com/webhook\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response (async via webhook):**\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_xyz789\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"dataset_size\": 100,\n  \"pass_rate\": 0.87,\n  \"results_url\": \"https://api.parse.news/v1/agents/eval/eval_xyz789/results\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"accuracy\": { \"mean\": 0.87, \"std\": 0.12, \"p50\": 0.90, \"p95\": 0.65 },\n    \"total_cost_usd\": 0.15,\n    \"total_duration_ms\": 45000\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.3 Datasets\n```\nPOST   /v1/agents/datasets              # Create dataset\nGET    /v1/agents/datasets              # List datasets\nGET    /v1/agents/datasets/:id          # Get dataset\nPUT    /v1/agents/datasets/:id          # Update dataset\nDELETE /v1/agents/datasets/:id          # Delete dataset"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":23,"aggregated":"# Parse for Agents — Implementation Plan\n\n*Created: March 5, 2026*\n*Goal: $1,500 MRR by Day 90*\n\n---\n\n## 1. Product Vision\n\n**Parse for Agents** is an API service that lets AI developers test, evaluate, and benchmark prompts in isolated sandbox environments. One API call = sandboxed execution + structured evaluation + scored results.\n\n**Tagline**: \"CI/CD for your prompts.\"\n\n### Why This Wins\n\nThe market has eval frameworks (PromptFoo, Braintrust, LangSmith) and sandbox runtimes (E2B, Modal). Nobody combines them. Parse already has:\n- Multi-LLM orchestration (4 providers, fallback chain)\n- BullMQ queue infrastructure\n- Credit/billing system with Stripe\n- API key management with scopes\n- Webhook delivery system\n\nWe're not starting from scratch — we're extending a production system.\n\n### Target Users\n1. **Agent builders** — Need to regression-test prompts before deploying agents\n2. **Prompt engineers** — Want structured evaluation beyond \"does it work?\"\n3. **AI startups** — Need automated prompt QA in CI/CD pipelines\n4. **Enterprise teams** — Compliance requirement to audit LLM outputs before production\n\n---\n\n## 2. Competitive Positioning\n\n| Competitor | What They Do | Gap |\n|-----------|-------------|-----|\n| **PromptFoo** | Local eval framework, YAML configs | No sandboxing, no hosted API, steep learning curve |\n| **Braintrust** | Logging + evals + datasets | Enterprise-priced ($500+/mo), no sandbox |\n| **LangSmith** | LangChain observability + evals | Tied to LangChain ecosystem |\n| **HumanLoop** | Prompt management + evals | No code execution, no sandbox |\n| **E2B** | Sandboxed code execution | No eval framework, just raw sandboxes |\n| **Arize Phoenix** | Tracing + evals | Post-hoc observability, not pre-deployment testing |\n\n### Our Niche\n**\"Sandboxed prompt evaluation as a service\"** — The missing middle between eval frameworks and sandbox runtimes. Ship a prompt test in one API call, get structured scores back.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Core API Design\n\n### Base URL\n```\nhttps://api.parse.news/v1/agents\n```\n\n### Authentication\nReuse existing Parse API key system (`parse_pk_prod_*` / `parse_pk_dev_*`). Add new scopes:\n- `prompt_test` — Run single prompt tests\n- `prompt_eval` — Run evaluation suites\n- `sandbox_exec` — Execute code in sandbox\n- `datasets` — Manage test datasets\n\n### Endpoints\n\n#### 3.1 Prompt Test (Core)\n```\nPOST /v1/agents/test\n```\nRun a single prompt against one or more LLM providers with structured evaluation.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": {\n    \"system\": \"You are a helpful assistant...\",\n    \"user\": \"Explain quantum computing in 3 sentences.\",\n    \"variables\": { \"topic\": \"quantum computing\", \"length\": 3 }\n  },\n  \"providers\": [\"deepseek-v3\", \"gpt-4o\", \"claude-sonnet\"],\n  \"eval\": {\n    \"criteria\": [\"relevance\", \"accuracy\", \"conciseness\", \"safety\"],\n    \"rubric\": \"Score 1-5 on each criterion\",\n    \"assertions\": [\n      { \"type\": \"contains\", \"value\": \"qubit\" },\n      { \"type\": \"max_tokens\", \"value\": 200 },\n      { \"type\": \"no_hallucination\", \"context\": \"...\" },\n      { \"type\": \"json_schema\", \"schema\": { ... } }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"sandbox\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"timeout_ms\": 30000,\n    \"memory_mb\": 256,\n    \"network\": false\n  },\n  \"options\": {\n    \"temperature\": 0.7,\n    \"max_tokens\": 500,\n    \"runs\": 3\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"test_abc123\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"duration_ms\": 4520,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"provider\": \"deepseek-v3\",\n      \"runs\": [\n        {\n          \"output\": \"Quantum computing uses qubits...\",\n          \"tokens\": { \"input\": 45, \"output\": 82 },\n          \"latency_ms\": 1200,\n          \"cost_usd\": 0.0003,\n          \"eval\": {\n            \"scores\": {\n              \"relevance\": 4.5,\n              \"accuracy\": 4.0,\n              \"conciseness\": 5.0,\n              \"safety\": 5.0\n            },\n            \"overall\": 4.6,\n            \"assertions\": [\n              { \"type\": \"contains\", \"value\": \"qubit\", \"passed\": true },\n              { \"type\": \"max_tokens\", \"value\": 200, \"passed\": true }\n            ],\n            \"pass\": true\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"aggregate\": {\n        \"avg_score\": 4.6,\n        \"avg_latency_ms\": 1180,\n        \"avg_cost_usd\": 0.0003,\n        \"pass_rate\": 1.0\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"comparison\": {\n    \"best_provider\": \"deepseek-v3\",\n    \"best_score\": 4.6,\n    \"cost_efficiency\": { \"deepseek-v3\": 15333, \"gpt-4o\": 230, \"claude-sonnet\": 460 }\n  },\n  \"credits_used\": 3\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2 Evaluation Suite\n```\nPOST /v1/agents/eval\n```\nRun a prompt against a dataset of test cases.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"prompt\": {\n    \"system\": \"Extract the sentiment...\",\n    \"user_template\": \"Analyze: {{text}}\"\n  },\n  \"dataset\": \"ds_sentiment_v2\",\n  \"providers\": [\"deepseek-v3\"],\n  \"eval\": {\n    \"criteria\": [\"accuracy\"],\n    \"ground_truth_field\": \"expected_sentiment\"\n  },\n  \"options\": {\n    \"concurrency\": 5,\n    \"webhook_url\": \"https://your-app.com/webhook\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response (async via webhook):**\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eval_xyz789\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"dataset_size\": 100,\n  \"pass_rate\": 0.87,\n  \"results_url\": \"https://api.parse.news/v1/agents/eval/eval_xyz789/results\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"accuracy\": { \"mean\": 0.87, \"std\": 0.12, \"p50\": 0.90, \"p95\": 0.65 },\n    \"total_cost_usd\": 0.15,\n    \"total_duration_ms\": 45000\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.3 Datasets\n```\nPOST   /v1/agents/datasets              # Create dataset\nGET    /v1/agents/datasets              # List datasets\nGET    /v1/agents/datasets/:id          # Get dataset\nPUT    /v1/agents/datasets/:id          # Update dataset\nDELETE /v1/agents/datasets/:id          # Delete dataset","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760617957}}
