Z.json:142:      \"id\": \"ff7a94dc-4cbe-4025-bd44-6405786c53be\",\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/load-tests/analyze.test.js:181:    if (response.status === 402) {\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/src/app/sources/[publication]/page.tsx:1024:      icon: <svg className=\"w-5 h-5\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path strokeLinecap=\"round\" strokeLinejoin=\"round\" strokeWidth={2} d=\"M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z\" /></svg>,\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/src/app/api/v1/bulk/analyze/route.ts:78:    return apiError('INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS', creditResult.error!, 402, {\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/src/app/api/v1/agents/[agent]/route.ts:139:    return apiError('INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS', creditResult.error!, 402, {\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/src/app/api/v1/route.ts:204:      paymentRequired: 402,\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/src/app/api/v1/article/rewrite/route.ts:71:    return apiError('INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS', creditResult.error!, 402, {\n/Users/kublai/projects/parse-github/src/app/api/v1/article/quick/route.ts:67:    return apiError('INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS', creditResult.error!, 402, {","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760633827}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ecca353","parentId":"4763a5c8","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:30:33.862Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5c5e474115454fadbba588e3","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LLM Provider Architecture\n\n## Direct API Integration System (UPDATED - Jan 28, 2026)\n\nThe system now uses **direct API integrations** with 4 providers in a cost-optimized fallback chain:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              LLM Provider Fallback Chain (Direct APIs)          │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Moonshot Kimi-k2.5 (Primary)  → DeepSeek (Secondary)            │\n│ $0.40/$1.75 per M             → $0.27/$0.41 per M               │\n│ 200 RPM excellent reasoning   → Best value + thinking           │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ MiniMax (Tertiary)            → Z.ai (Overflow)                  │\n│ $0.28/$1.20 per M             → $0.60/$2.20 per M               │\n│ 500 RPM capacity             → ~5-10 RPM only                    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Provider Priority Order (Jan 27, 2026)\n\n| Priority | Provider | Input Cost | Output Cost | RPM | Thinking Mode | API Key |\n|----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----|---------------|---------|\n| 1 | Moonshot Kimi-k2.5 | $0.40/M | $1.75/M | 200 | ❌ No | `MOONSHOT_API_KEY` |\n| 2 | DeepSeek V3.2 Speciale | $0.27/M | $0.41/M | Unlimited | ✅ Yes | `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY` |\n| 3 | MiniMax M2 | $0.28/M | $1.20/M | 500 | ❌ No | `MINIMAX_API_KEY` |\n| 4 | Z.ai GLM-4.7 | $0.60/M | $2.20/M | ~5-10 | ❌ No | `ZAI_API_KEY` |\n\n### DeepSeek Thinking Mode\n\nDeepSeek supports extended reasoning via chain-of-thought:\n\n```typescript\nimport { callLLMWithProvider } from '@/lib/llm';\n\nconst result = await callLLMWithProvider({\n  provider: 'deepseek',\n  thinkingMode: true,  // Enable chain-of-thought reasoning\n  systemPrompt: 'Analyze carefully...',\n  userPrompt: content,\n});\n\n// Returns both reasoning and final answer\n// result.content includes <reasoning> tags with chain of thought\n```\n\n### Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `deepseek.ts` | DeepSeek API integration with thinking mode (NEW) |\n| `minimax.ts` | MiniMax M2 API integration (direct) |\n| `moonshot.ts` | Moonshot Kimi-k2.5 API integration (direct - Primary) |\n| `zai.ts` | Z.ai GLM-4.7 API integration (direct) |\n| `llm.ts` | Unified provider abstraction with automatic fallback |\n| `search-quota.ts` | Search API quota tracking with warning alerts (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/query-dedup.ts` | Query normalization and deduplication (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/search-cache.ts` | Redis-backed persistent search cache (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/semantic-batch.ts` | Semantic query clustering (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/claim-cache.ts` | Claim verification caching (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/searxng-provider.ts` | SearXNG API integration (self-hosted search) (NEW - Jan 27) |\n| `search/searxng-pool.ts` | Round-robin pool with health checks (NEW - Jan 27) |\n| `search/searxng-health.ts` | Health monitoring utilities (NEW - Jan 27) |\n| `../../docs/plans/throughput.md` | Comprehensive throughput design with queue strategy, fallback patterns, and capacity projections |\n\n### Auto-Enabled Thinking Mode\n\nAs of Jan 19, 2026, **DeepSeek thinking mode is automatically enabled** for all agent calls when using DeepSeek as the provider. This provides higher-quality reasoning without requiring explicit `thinkingMode: true` parameter passing.\n\n```typescript\n// In llm.ts - effectiveThinkingMode is set automatically\nconst effectiveThinkingMode = provider === 'deepseek' ? true : thinkingMode;\n```\n\n**Note:** Moonshot Kimi-k2.5 (primary provider) does not currently support thinking mode. Thinking mode is available when the system falls back to DeepSeek (secondary).\n\n---\n\n## Performance Optimizations (Jan 19, 2026)\n\nAnalysis pipeline optimized from **~10.8 minutes to ~5 minutes** (54% faster).\n\n| Optimization | Impact | Implementation |\n|-------------|---------|----------------|\n| DeepSeek Primary | ~220s saved | Bypass failing MiniMax fallback chain |\n| Parallel Fact-Checking | ~300s saved | All claims verified simultaneously |\n| Parallel Search Providers | ~20s saved | Race mode with 3 providers |\n| Removed Cooldown | ~3s saved | Eliminated Z.ai 3s delay |\n| Search Result Caching | Variable | 5-minute TTL in SearchManager |\n| **Search Throughput Phase 1-2** (NEW - Jan 25) | **Cost reduction** | See below |\n\n### Search Throughput Optimization (NEW - Jan 25, 2026)\n\nPhase 1 & 2 implementation for reducing API costs:\n\n| Feature | Cost Impact | Implementation |\n|---------|-------------|----------------|\n| Query Deduplication | 20-30% reduction | `search/query-dedup.ts` - Normalize and dedupe similar queries |\n| Redis Persistent Cache | Variable | `search/search-cache.ts` - Survives restarts |"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"# LLM Provider Architecture\n\n## Direct API Integration System (UPDATED - Jan 28, 2026)\n\nThe system now uses **direct API integrations** with 4 providers in a cost-optimized fallback chain:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              LLM Provider Fallback Chain (Direct APIs)          │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Moonshot Kimi-k2.5 (Primary)  → DeepSeek (Secondary)            │\n│ $0.40/$1.75 per M             → $0.27/$0.41 per M               │\n│ 200 RPM excellent reasoning   → Best value + thinking           │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ MiniMax (Tertiary)            → Z.ai (Overflow)                  │\n│ $0.28/$1.20 per M             → $0.60/$2.20 per M               │\n│ 500 RPM capacity             → ~5-10 RPM only                    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Provider Priority Order (Jan 27, 2026)\n\n| Priority | Provider | Input Cost | Output Cost | RPM | Thinking Mode | API Key |\n|----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----|---------------|---------|\n| 1 | Moonshot Kimi-k2.5 | $0.40/M | $1.75/M | 200 | ❌ No | `MOONSHOT_API_KEY` |\n| 2 | DeepSeek V3.2 Speciale | $0.27/M | $0.41/M | Unlimited | ✅ Yes | `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY` |\n| 3 | MiniMax M2 | $0.28/M | $1.20/M | 500 | ❌ No | `MINIMAX_API_KEY` |\n| 4 | Z.ai GLM-4.7 | $0.60/M | $2.20/M | ~5-10 | ❌ No | `ZAI_API_KEY` |\n\n### DeepSeek Thinking Mode\n\nDeepSeek supports extended reasoning via chain-of-thought:\n\n```typescript\nimport { callLLMWithProvider } from '@/lib/llm';\n\nconst result = await callLLMWithProvider({\n  provider: 'deepseek',\n  thinkingMode: true,  // Enable chain-of-thought reasoning\n  systemPrompt: 'Analyze carefully...',\n  userPrompt: content,\n});\n\n// Returns both reasoning and final answer\n// result.content includes <reasoning> tags with chain of thought\n```\n\n### Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `deepseek.ts` | DeepSeek API integration with thinking mode (NEW) |\n| `minimax.ts` | MiniMax M2 API integration (direct) |\n| `moonshot.ts` | Moonshot Kimi-k2.5 API integration (direct - Primary) |\n| `zai.ts` | Z.ai GLM-4.7 API integration (direct) |\n| `llm.ts` | Unified provider abstraction with automatic fallback |\n| `search-quota.ts` | Search API quota tracking with warning alerts (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/query-dedup.ts` | Query normalization and deduplication (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/search-cache.ts` | Redis-backed persistent search cache (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/semantic-batch.ts` | Semantic query clustering (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/claim-cache.ts` | Claim verification caching (NEW - Jan 25) |\n| `search/searxng-provider.ts` | SearXNG API integration (self-hosted search) (NEW - Jan 27) |\n| `search/searxng-pool.ts` | Round-robin pool with health checks (NEW - Jan 27) |\n| `search/searxng-health.ts` | Health monitoring utilities (NEW - Jan 27) |\n| `../../docs/plans/throughput.md` | Comprehensive throughput design with queue strategy, fallback patterns, and capacity projections |\n\n### Auto-Enabled Thinking Mode\n\nAs of Jan 19, 2026, **DeepSeek thinking mode is automatically enabled** for all agent calls when using DeepSeek as the provider. This provides higher-quality reasoning without requiring explicit `thinkingMode: true` parameter passing.\n\n```typescript\n// In llm.ts - effectiveThinkingMode is set automatically\nconst effectiveThinkingMode = provider === 'deepseek' ? true : thinkingMode;\n```\n\n**Note:** Moonshot Kimi-k2.5 (primary provider) does not currently support thinking mode. Thinking mode is available when the system falls back to DeepSeek (secondary).\n\n---\n\n## Performance Optimizations (Jan 19, 2026)\n\nAnalysis pipeline optimized from **~10.8 minutes to ~5 minutes** (54% faster).\n\n| Optimization | Impact | Implementation |\n|-------------|---------|----------------|\n| DeepSeek Primary | ~220s saved | Bypass failing MiniMax fallback chain |\n| Parallel Fact-Checking | ~300s saved | All claims verified simultaneously |\n| Parallel Search Providers | ~20s saved | Race mode with 3 providers |\n| Removed Cooldown | ~3s saved | Eliminated Z.ai 3s delay |\n| Search Result Caching | Variable | 5-minute TTL in SearchManager |\n| **Search Throughput Phase 1-2** (NEW - Jan 25) | **Cost reduction** | See below |\n\n### Search Throughput Optimization (NEW - Jan 25, 2026)\n\nPhase 1 & 2 implementation for reducing API costs:\n\n| Feature | Cost Impact | Implementation |\n|---------|-------------|----------------|\n| Query Deduplication | 20-30% reduction | `search/query-dedup.ts` - Normalize and dedupe similar queries |\n| Redis Persistent Cache | Variable | `search/search-cache.ts` - Survives restarts |","cwd":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772760633854}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9730fbb","parentId":"3ecca353","timestamp":"2026-03-06T01:30:46.593Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - the search for \"x402\" in the project only found HTTP 402 status codes (Payment Required), not the x402 payment protocol. The x402 protocol is a different thing - it's an HTTP-based payment protocol from Coinbase that allows services to charge per API call using cryptocurrency (USDC).\n\nLet me check if there's any mention of x402 in the agent skills or other context files.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"I see that the search for \"x402\" only returns HTTP 402 status codes, not the x402 payment protocol. Let me check if there's any x402-related context in the agent files or if this is a new request."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ba4a015fef5a42bbb32c9bdf","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"x402\\|coinbase\\|pay.per.use\\|usdc\" ~/.openclaw/agents/main/ --include=\"*.md\" --include=\"*.txt\" 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_29042e6318204b21836eb73d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/agents/temujin/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"zai-coding","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":15665,"output":230,"cacheRead":29952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45847,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772760633863}}
